1292 
1293 bool RegisterAllocationData::ExistsUseWithoutDefinition() {
1294  bool found = false;
1295  for (int operand_index : *live_in_sets()[0]) {
1296  found = true;
1297  PrintF("Register allocator error: live v%d reached first block.\n",
1298  operand_index);
1299  LiveRange* range = GetLiveRangeFor(operand_index);
1300  PrintF(" (first use is at position %d in instruction %d)\n",
1301  range->positions().first()->pos().value(),
1302  range->positions().first()->pos().ToInstructionIndex());
1303  if (debug_name() == nullptr) {
1304  PrintF("\n");
1305  } else {
1306  PrintF(" (function: %s)\n", debug_name());
1307  }
1308  }
1309  return found;
1310 }
1311 
1312 // If a range is defined in a deferred block, we can expect all the range
1313 // to only cover positions in deferred blocks. Otherwise, a block on the
1314 // hot path would be dominated by a deferred block, meaning it is unreachable
1315 // without passing through the deferred block, which is contradictory.
1316 // In particular, when such a range contributes a result back on the hot
1317 // path, it will be as one of the inputs of a phi. In that case, the value
1318 // will be transferred via a move in the Gap::END's of the last instruction
1319 // of a deferred block.
1320 bool RegisterAllocationData::RangesDefinedInDeferredStayInDeferred() {
1321  const size_t live_ranges_size = live_ranges().size();
1322  for (const TopLevelLiveRange* range : live_ranges()) {
1323  CHECK_EQ(live_ranges_size,
1324  live_ranges().size()); // TODO(neis): crbug.com/831822
1325  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(range);
1326  if (range->IsEmpty() ||
1327  !code()
1328  ->GetInstructionBlock(range->Start().ToInstructionIndex())
1329  ->IsDeferred()) {
1330  continue;
1331  }
1332  for (const UseInterval& interval : range->intervals()) {
1333  int first = interval.FirstGapIndex();
1334  int last = interval.LastGapIndex();
1335  for (int instr = first; instr <= last;) {
1336  const InstructionBlock* block = code()->GetInstructionBlock(instr);
1337  if (!block->IsDeferred()) return false;
1338  instr = block->last_instruction_index() + 1;
1339  }
1340  }
1341  }
1342  return true;
1343 }
1344 
1345 SpillRange* RegisterAllocationData::AssignSpillRangeToLiveRange(
1346  TopLevelLiveRange* range, SpillMode spill_mode) {
1347  using SpillType = TopLevelLiveRange::SpillType;
1348  DCHECK(!range->HasSpillOperand());
1349 
1350  SpillRange* spill_range = range->GetAllocatedSpillRange();
1351  if (spill_range == nullptr) {
1352  spill_range = allocation_zone()->New<SpillRange>(range, allocation_zone());
1353  }
1354  if (spill_mode == SpillMode::kSpillDeferred &&
1355  (range->spill_type() != SpillType::kSpillRange)) {
1356  range->set_spill_type(SpillType::kDeferredSpillRange);
1357  } else {
1358  range->set_spill_type(SpillType::kSpillRange);
1359  }
1360 
1361  return spill_range;
1362 }
1363 
1364 void RegisterAllocationData::MarkFixedUse(MachineRepresentation rep,
1365  int index) {
1366  switch (rep) {
1367  case MachineRepresentation::kFloat16:
1368  case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
1369  case MachineRepresentation::kSimd128:
1370  case MachineRepresentation::kSimd256:
1371  if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kOverlap) {
1372  fixed_fp_register_use_->Add(index);
1373  } else if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kIndependent) {
1374  if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kFloat16 ||
1375  rep == MachineRepresentation::kFloat32) {
1376  fixed_fp_register_use_->Add(index);
1377  } else {
1378  fixed_simd128_register_use_->Add(index);
1379  }
1380  } else {
1381  int alias_base_index = -1;
1382  int aliases = config()->GetAliases(
1383  rep, index, MachineRepresentation::kFloat64, &alias_base_index);
1384  DCHECK(aliases > 0 || (aliases == 0 && alias_base_index == -1));
1385  while (aliases--) {
1386  int aliased_reg = alias_base_index + aliases;
1387  fixed_fp_register_use_->Add(aliased_reg);
1388  }
1389  }
1390  break;
1391  case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64:
1392  fixed_fp_register_use_->Add(index);
1393  break;
1394  default:
1395  DCHECK(!IsFloatingPoint(rep));
1396  fixed_register_use_->Add(index);
1397  break;
1398  }
1399 }
1400 
1401 bool RegisterAllocationData::HasFixedUse(MachineRepresentation rep, int index) {
1402  switch (rep) {
1403  case MachineRepresentation::kFloat16:
1404  case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
1405  case MachineRepresentation::kSimd128:
1406  case MachineRepresentation::kSimd256: {
1407  if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kOverlap) {
1408  return fixed_fp_register_use_->Contains(index);
1409  } else if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kIndependent) {
1410  if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kFloat16 ||
1411  rep == MachineRepresentation::kFloat32) {
1412  return fixed_fp_register_use_->Contains(index);
1413  } else {
1414  return fixed_simd128_register_use_->Contains(index);
1415  }
1416  } else {
1417  int alias_base_index = -1;
1418  int aliases = config()->GetAliases(
1419  rep, index, MachineRepresentation::kFloat64, &alias_base_index);
1420  DCHECK(aliases > 0 || (aliases == 0 && alias_base_index == -1));
1421  bool result = false;
1422  while (aliases-- && !result) {
1423  int aliased_reg = alias_base_index + aliases;
1424  result |= fixed_fp_register_use_->Contains(aliased_reg);
1425  }
1426  return result;
1427  }
1428  }
1429  case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64:
1430  return fixed_fp_register_use_->Contains(index);
1431  default:
1432  DCHECK(!IsFloatingPoint(rep));
1433  return fixed_register_use_->Contains(index);
1434  }
1435 }
1436 
1437 void RegisterAllocationData::MarkAllocated(MachineRepresentation rep,
1438  int index) {
1439  switch (rep) {
1440  case MachineRepresentation::kFloat16:
1441  case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
1442  case MachineRepresentation::kSimd128:
1443  case MachineRepresentation::kSimd256:
1444  if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kOverlap) {
1445  assigned_double_registers_->Add(index);
1446  } else if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kIndependent) {
1447  if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kFloat16 ||
1448  rep == MachineRepresentation::kFloat32) {
1449  assigned_double_registers_->Add(index);
1450  } else {
1451  assigned_simd128_registers_->Add(index);
1452  }
1453  } else {
1454  int alias_base_index = -1;
1455  int aliases = config()->GetAliases(
1456  rep, index, MachineRepresentation::kFloat64, &alias_base_index);
1457  DCHECK(aliases > 0 || (aliases == 0 && alias_base_index == -1));
1458  while (aliases--) {
1459  int aliased_reg = alias_base_index + aliases;
1460  assigned_double_registers_->Add(aliased_reg);
1461  }
1462  }
1463  break;
1464  case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64:
1465  assigned_double_registers_->Add(index);
1466  break;
1467  default:
1468  DCHECK(!IsFloatingPoint(rep));
1469  assigned_registers_->Add(index);
1470  break;
1471  }
1472 }
1473 
1474 bool RegisterAllocationData::IsBlockBoundary(LifetimePosition pos) const {
1475  return pos.IsFullStart() &&
1476  (static_cast<size_t>(pos.ToInstructionIndex()) ==
1477  code()->instructions().size() ||
1478  code()->GetInstructionBlock(pos.ToInstructionIndex())->code_start() ==
1479  pos.ToInstructionIndex());
1480 }
1481 
1482 ConstraintBuilder::ConstraintBuilder(RegisterAllocationData* data)
1483  : data_(data) {}
1484 
1485 InstructionOperand* ConstraintBuilder::AllocateFixed(
1486  UnallocatedOperand* operand, int pos, bool is_tagged, bool is_input,
1487  bool is_output) {
1488  TRACE("Allocating fixed reg for op %d\n", operand->virtual_register());
1489  DCHECK(operand->HasFixedPolicy());
1490  InstructionOperand allocated;
1491  MachineRepresentation rep = InstructionSequence::DefaultRepresentation();
1492  int virtual_register = operand->virtual_register();
1493  if (virtual_register != InstructionOperand::kInvalidVirtualRegister) {
1494  rep = data()->RepresentationFor(virtual_register);
1495  }
1496  if (operand->HasFixedSlotPolicy()) {
1497  allocated = AllocatedOperand(AllocatedOperand::STACK_SLOT, rep,
1498  operand->fixed_slot_index());
1499  } else if (operand->HasFixedRegisterPolicy()) {
1500  DCHECK(!IsFloatingPoint(rep));
1501  DCHECK_IMPLIES(is_input || is_output,
1502  data()->config()->IsAllocatableGeneralCode(
1503  operand->fixed_register_index()));
1504  allocated = AllocatedOperand(AllocatedOperand::REGISTER, rep,
1505  operand->fixed_register_index());
1506  } else if (operand->HasFixedFPRegisterPolicy()) {
1507  DCHECK(IsFloatingPoint(rep));
1508  DCHECK_NE(InstructionOperand::kInvalidVirtualRegister, virtual_register);
1509  if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kFloat16 ||
1510  rep == MachineRepresentation::kFloat32) {
1511  DCHECK_IMPLIES(is_input || is_output,
1512  data()->config()->IsAllocatableFloatCode(
1513  operand->fixed_register_index()));
1514  } else if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kFloat64) {
1515  DCHECK_IMPLIES(is_input || is_output,
1516  data()->config()->IsAllocatableDoubleCode(
1517  operand->fixed_register_index()));
1518  } else if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kSimd128) {
1519  DCHECK_IMPLIES(is_input || is_output,
1520  data()->config()->IsAllocatableSimd128Code(
1521  operand->fixed_register_index()));
1522 #ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_X64
1523  // The ExtractF128 node with lane 0 to Simd128 maybe elided as alias to
1524  // the corresponding Simd256 ymm register on x64.
1525  } else if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kSimd256) {
1526  DCHECK_IMPLIES(is_input || is_output,
1527  data()->config()->IsAllocatableSimd256Code(
1528  operand->fixed_register_index()));
1529 #endif
1530  } else {
1531  UNREACHABLE();
1532  }
1533  allocated = AllocatedOperand(AllocatedOperand::REGISTER, rep,
1534  operand->fixed_register_index());
1535  } else {
1536  UNREACHABLE();
1537  }
1538  if (is_input && allocated.IsAnyRegister()) {
1539  data()->MarkFixedUse(rep, operand->fixed_register_index());
1540  }
1541  InstructionOperand::ReplaceWith(operand, &allocated);
1542  if (is_tagged) {
1543  TRACE("Fixed reg is tagged at %d\n", pos);
1544  Instruction* instr = code()->InstructionAt(pos);
1545  if (instr->HasReferenceMap()) {
1546  instr->reference_map()->RecordReference(*AllocatedOperand::cast(operand));
1547  }
1548  }
1549  return operand;
1550 }
1551 
1552 void ConstraintBuilder::MeetRegisterConstraints() {
1553  for (InstructionBlock* block : code()->instruction_blocks()) {
1554  data_->tick_counter()->TickAndMaybeEnterSafepoint();
1555  MeetRegisterConstraints(block);
1556  }
1557 }
1558 
1559 void ConstraintBuilder::MeetRegisterConstraints(const InstructionBlock* block) {
1560  int start = block->first_instruction_index();
1561  int end = block->last_instruction_index();
1562  DCHECK_NE(-1, start);
1563  for (int i = start; i <= end; ++i) {
1564  MeetConstraintsBefore(i);
1565  if (i != end) MeetConstraintsAfter(i);
1566  }
1567  // Meet register constraints for the instruction in the end.
1568  MeetRegisterConstraintsForLastInstructionInBlock(block);
1569 }
1570 
1571 void ConstraintBuilder::MeetRegisterConstraintsForLastInstructionInBlock(
1572  const InstructionBlock* block) {
1573  int end = block->last_instruction_index();
1574  Instruction* last_instruction = code()->InstructionAt(end);
1575  for (size_t i = 0; i < last_instruction->OutputCount(); i++) {
1576  InstructionOperand* output_operand = last_instruction->OutputAt(i);
1577  DCHECK(!output_operand->IsConstant());
1578  UnallocatedOperand* output = UnallocatedOperand::cast(output_operand);
1579  int output_vreg = output->virtual_register();
1580  TopLevelLiveRange* range = data()->GetLiveRangeFor(output_vreg);
1581  bool assigned = false;
1582  if (output->HasFixedPolicy()) {
1583  AllocateFixed(output, -1, false, false, true);
1584  // This value is produced on the stack, we never need to spill it.
1585  if (output->IsStackSlot()) {
1586  DCHECK(LocationOperand::cast(output)->index() <
1587  data()->frame()->GetSpillSlotCount());
1588  range->SetSpillOperand(LocationOperand::cast(output));
1589  range->SetSpillStartIndex(end);
1590  assigned = true;
1591  }
1592 
1593  for (const RpoNumber& succ : block->successors()) {
1594  const InstructionBlock* successor = code()->InstructionBlockAt(succ);
1595  DCHECK_EQ(1, successor->PredecessorCount());
1596  int gap_index = successor->first_instruction_index();
1597  // Create an unconstrained operand for the same virtual register
1598  // and insert a gap move from the fixed output to the operand.
1599  UnallocatedOperand output_copy(UnallocatedOperand::REGISTER_OR_SLOT,
1600  output_vreg);
1601  data()->AddGapMove(gap_index, Instruction::START, *output, output_copy);
1602  }
1603  }
1604 
1605  if (!assigned) {
1606  for (const RpoNumber& succ : block->successors()) {
1607  const InstructionBlock* successor = code()->InstructionBlockAt(succ);
1608  DCHECK_EQ(1, successor->PredecessorCount());
1609  int gap_index = successor->first_instruction_index();
1610  range->RecordSpillLocation(allocation_zone(), gap_index, output);
1611  range->SetSpillStartIndex(gap_index);
1612  }
1613  }
1614  }
1615 }
1616 
1617 void ConstraintBuilder::MeetConstraintsAfter(int instr_index) {
1618  Instruction* first = code()->InstructionAt(instr_index);
1619  // Handle fixed temporaries.
1620  for (size_t i = 0; i < first->TempCount(); i++) {
1621  UnallocatedOperand* temp = UnallocatedOperand::cast(first->TempAt(i));
1622  if (temp->HasFixedPolicy())
1623  AllocateFixed(temp, instr_index, false, false, false);
1624  }
1625  // Handle constant/fixed output operands.
1626  for (size_t i = 0; i < first->OutputCount(); i++) {
1627  InstructionOperand* output = first->OutputAt(i);
1628  if (output->IsConstant()) {
1629  int output_vreg = ConstantOperand::cast(output)->virtual_register();
1630  TopLevelLiveRange* range = data()->GetLiveRangeFor(output_vreg);
1631  range->SetSpillStartIndex(instr_index + 1);
1632  range->SetSpillOperand(output);
1633  continue;
1634  }
1635  UnallocatedOperand* first_output = UnallocatedOperand::cast(output);
1636  TopLevelLiveRange* range =
1637  data()->GetLiveRangeFor(first_output->virtual_register());
1638  bool assigned = false;
1639  if (first_output->HasFixedPolicy()) {
1640  int output_vreg = first_output->virtual_register();
1641  UnallocatedOperand output_copy(UnallocatedOperand::REGISTER_OR_SLOT,
1642  output_vreg);
1643  bool is_tagged = code()->IsReference(output_vreg);
1644  if (first_output->HasSecondaryStorage()) {
1645  range->MarkHasPreassignedSlot();
1646  data()->preassigned_slot_ranges().push_back(
1647  std::make_pair(range, first_output->GetSecondaryStorage()));
1648  }
1649  AllocateFixed(first_output, instr_index, is_tagged, false, true);
1650 
1651  // This value is produced on the stack, we never need to spill it.
1652  if (first_output->IsStackSlot()) {
1653  DCHECK(LocationOperand::cast(first_output)->index() <
1654  data()->frame()->GetTotalFrameSlotCount());
1655  range->SetSpillOperand(LocationOperand::cast(first_output));
1656  range->SetSpillStartIndex(instr_index + 1);
1657  assigned = true;
1658  }
1659  data()->AddGapMove(instr_index + 1, Instruction::START, *first_output,
1660  output_copy);
1661  }
1662  // Make sure we add a gap move for spilling (if we have not done
1663  // so already).
1664  if (!assigned) {
1665  range->RecordSpillLocation(allocation_zone(), instr_index + 1,
1666  first_output);
1667  range->SetSpillStartIndex(instr_index + 1);
1668  }
1669  }
1670 }
1671 
1672 void ConstraintBuilder::MeetConstraintsBefore(int instr_index) {
1673  Instruction* second = code()->InstructionAt(instr_index);
1674  // Handle fixed input operands of second instruction.
1675  ZoneVector<TopLevelLiveRange*>* spilled_consts = nullptr;
1676  for (size_t i = 0; i < second->InputCount(); i++) {
1677  InstructionOperand* input = second->InputAt(i);
1678  if (input->IsImmediate()) {
1679  continue; // Ignore immediates.
1680  }
1681  UnallocatedOperand* cur_input = UnallocatedOperand::cast(input);
1682  if (cur_input->HasSlotPolicy()) {
1683  TopLevelLiveRange* range =
1684  data()->GetLiveRangeFor(cur_input->virtual_register());
1685  if (range->HasSpillOperand() && range->GetSpillOperand()->IsConstant()) {
1686  bool already_spilled = false;
1687  if (spilled_consts == nullptr) {
1688  spilled_consts =
1689  allocation_zone()->New<ZoneVector<TopLevelLiveRange*>>(
1690  allocation_zone());
1691  } else {
1692  auto it =
1693  std::find(spilled_consts->begin(), spilled_consts->end(), range);
1694  already_spilled = it != spilled_consts->end();
1695  }
1696  auto it = data()->slot_for_const_range().find(range);
1697  if (it == data()->slot_for_const_range().end()) {
1698  DCHECK(!already_spilled);
1699  int width = ByteWidthForStackSlot(range->representation());
1700  int index = data()->frame()->AllocateSpillSlot(width);
1701  auto* slot = AllocatedOperand::New(allocation_zone(),
1702  LocationOperand::STACK_SLOT,
1703  range->representation(), index);
1704  it = data()->slot_for_const_range().emplace(range, slot).first;
1705  }
1706  if (!already_spilled) {
1707  auto* slot = it->second;
1708  int input_vreg = cur_input->virtual_register();
1709  UnallocatedOperand input_copy(UnallocatedOperand::REGISTER_OR_SLOT,
1710  input_vreg);
1711  // Spill at every use position for simplicity, this case is very rare.
1712  data()->AddGapMove(instr_index, Instruction::END, input_copy, *slot);
1713  spilled_consts->push_back(range);
1714  }
1715  }
1716  }
1717  if (cur_input->HasFixedPolicy()) {
1718  int input_vreg = cur_input->virtual_register();
1719  UnallocatedOperand input_copy(UnallocatedOperand::REGISTER_OR_SLOT,
1720  input_vreg);
1721  bool is_tagged = code()->IsReference(input_vreg);
1722  AllocateFixed(cur_input, instr_index, is_tagged, true, false);
1723  data()->AddGapMove(instr_index, Instruction::END, input_copy, *cur_input);
1724  }
1725  }
1726  // Handle "output same as input" for second instruction.
1727  for (size_t i = 0; i < second->OutputCount(); i++) {
1728  InstructionOperand* output = second->OutputAt(i);
1729  if (!output->IsUnallocated()) continue;
1730  UnallocatedOperand* second_output = UnallocatedOperand::cast(output);
1731  if (!second_output->HasSameAsInputPolicy()) continue;
1732  DCHECK_EQ(0, i); // Only valid for first output.
1733  UnallocatedOperand* cur_input =
1734  UnallocatedOperand::cast(second->InputAt(second_output->input_index()));
1735  int output_vreg = second_output->virtual_register();
1736  int input_vreg = cur_input->virtual_register();
1737  UnallocatedOperand input_copy(UnallocatedOperand::REGISTER_OR_SLOT,
1738  input_vreg);
1739  *cur_input =
1740  UnallocatedOperand(*cur_input, second_output->virtual_register());
1741  MoveOperands* gap_move = data()->AddGapMove(instr_index, Instruction::END,
1742  input_copy, *cur_input);
1743  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(gap_move);
1744  if (code()->IsReference(input_vreg) && !code()->IsReference(output_vreg)) {
1745  if (second->HasReferenceMap()) {
1746  RegisterAllocationData::DelayedReference delayed_reference = {
1747  second->reference_map(), &gap_move->source()};
1748  data()->delayed_references().push_back(delayed_reference);
1749  }
1750  }
1751  }
1752 }
1753 
1754 void ConstraintBuilder::ResolvePhis() {
1755  // Process the blocks in reverse order.
1756  for (InstructionBlock* block : base::Reversed(code()->instruction_blocks())) {
1757  data_->tick_counter()->TickAndMaybeEnterSafepoint();
1758  ResolvePhis(block);
1759  }
1760 }
1761 
1762 void ConstraintBuilder::ResolvePhis(const InstructionBlock* block) {
1763  for (PhiInstruction* phi : block->phis()) {
1764  int phi_vreg = phi->virtual_register();
1765  RegisterAllocationData::PhiMapValue* map_value =
1766  data()->InitializePhiMap(block, phi);
1767  InstructionOperand& output = phi->output();
1768  // Map the destination operands, so the commitment phase can find them.
1769  for (size_t i = 0; i < phi->operands().size(); ++i) {
1770  InstructionBlock* cur_block =
1771  code()->InstructionBlockAt(block->predecessors()[i]);
1772  UnallocatedOperand input(UnallocatedOperand::REGISTER_OR_SLOT,
1773  phi->operands()[i]);
1774  MoveOperands* move = data()->AddGapMove(
1775  cur_block->last_instruction_index(), Instruction::END, input, output);
1776  map_value->AddOperand(&move->destination());
1777  DCHECK(!code()
1778  ->InstructionAt(cur_block->last_instruction_index())
1779  ->HasReferenceMap());
1780  }
1781  TopLevelLiveRange* live_range = data()->GetLiveRangeFor(phi_vreg);
1782  int gap_index = block->first_instruction_index();
1783  live_range->RecordSpillLocation(allocation_zone(), gap_index, &output);
1784  live_range->SetSpillStartIndex(gap_index);
1785  // We use the phi-ness of some nodes in some later heuristics.
1786  live_range->set_is_phi(true);
1787  live_range->set_is_non_loop_phi(!block->IsLoopHeader());
1788  }
1789 }
1790 
1791 LiveRangeBuilder::LiveRangeBuilder(RegisterAllocationData* data,
1792  Zone* local_zone)
1793  : data_(data), phi_hints_(local_zone) {}
1794 
1795 SparseBitVector* LiveRangeBuilder::ComputeLiveOut(
1796  const InstructionBlock* block, RegisterAllocationData* data) {
1797  size_t block_index = block->rpo_number().ToSize();
1798  SparseBitVector* live_out = data->live_out_sets()[block_index];
1799  if (live_out == nullptr) {
1800  // Compute live out for the given block, except not including backward
1801  // successor edges.
1802  Zone* zone = data->allocation_zone();
1803  const InstructionSequence* code = data->code();
1804 
1805  live_out = zone->New<SparseBitVector>(zone);
1806 
1807  // Process all successor blocks.
1808  for (const RpoNumber& succ : block->successors()) {
1809  // Add values live on entry to the successor.
1810  if (succ <= block->rpo_number()) continue;
1811  SparseBitVector* live_in = data->live_in_sets()[succ.ToSize()];
1812  if (live_in != nullptr) live_out->Union(*live_in);
1813 
1814  // All phi input operands corresponding to this successor edge are live
1815  // out from this block.
1816  const InstructionBlock* successor = code->InstructionBlockAt(succ);
1817  size_t index = successor->PredecessorIndexOf(block->rpo_number());
1818  DCHECK(index < successor->PredecessorCount());
1819  for (PhiInstruction* phi : successor->phis()) {
1820  live_out->Add(phi->operands()[index]);
1821  }
1822  }
1823  data->live_out_sets()[block_index] = live_out;
1824  }
1825  return live_out;
1826 }
1827 
1828 void LiveRangeBuilder::AddInitialIntervals(const InstructionBlock* block,
1829  SparseBitVector* live_out) {
1830  // Add an interval that includes the entire block to the live range for
1831  // each live_out value.
1832  LifetimePosition start = LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(
1833  block->first_instruction_index());
1834  LifetimePosition end = LifetimePosition::InstructionFromInstructionIndex(
1835  block->last_instruction_index())
1836  .NextStart();
1837  for (int operand_index : *live_out) {
1838  TopLevelLiveRange* range = data()->GetLiveRangeFor(operand_index);
1839  range->AddUseInterval(start, end, allocation_zone());
1840  }
1841 }
1842 
1843 int LiveRangeBuilder::FixedFPLiveRangeID(int index, MachineRepresentation rep) {
1844  int result = -index - 1;
1845  switch (rep) {
1846  case MachineRepresentation::kSimd256:
1847  result -=
1848  kNumberOfFixedRangesPerRegister * config()->num_simd128_registers();
1849  [[fallthrough]];
1850  case MachineRepresentation::kSimd128:
1851  result -=
1852  kNumberOfFixedRangesPerRegister * config()->num_float_registers();
1853  [[fallthrough]];
1854  case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
1855  result -=
1856  kNumberOfFixedRangesPerRegister * config()->num_double_registers();
1857  [[fallthrough]];
1858  case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64:
1859  result -=
1860  kNumberOfFixedRangesPerRegister * config()->num_general_registers();
1861  break;
1862  default:
1863  UNREACHABLE();
1864  }
1865  return result;
1866 }
1867 
1868 TopLevelLiveRange* LiveRangeBuilder::FixedLiveRangeFor(int index,
1869  SpillMode spill_mode) {
1870  int offset = spill_mode == SpillMode::kSpillAtDefinition
1871  ? 0
1872  : config()->num_general_registers();
1873  DCHECK(index < config()->num_general_registers());
1874  TopLevelLiveRange* result = data()->fixed_live_ranges()[offset + index];
1875  if (result == nullptr) {
1876  MachineRepresentation rep = InstructionSequence::DefaultRepresentation();
1877  result = data()->NewLiveRange(FixedLiveRangeID(offset + index), rep);
1878  DCHECK(result->IsFixed());
1879  result->set_assigned_register(index);
1880  data()->MarkAllocated(rep, index);
1881  if (spill_mode == SpillMode::kSpillDeferred) {
1882  result->set_deferred_fixed();
1883  }
1884  data()->fixed_live_ranges()[offset + index] = result;
1885  }
1886  return result;
1887 }
1888 
1889 TopLevelLiveRange* LiveRangeBuilder::FixedFPLiveRangeFor(
1890  int index, MachineRepresentation rep, SpillMode spill_mode) {
1891  int num_regs = config()->num_double_registers();
1892  ZoneVector<TopLevelLiveRange*>* live_ranges =
1893  &data()->fixed_double_live_ranges();
1894  if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kCombine) {
1895  switch (rep) {
1896  case MachineRepresentation::kFloat16:
1897  case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
1898  num_regs = config()->num_float_registers();
1899  live_ranges = &data()->fixed_float_live_ranges();
1900  break;
1901  case MachineRepresentation::kSimd128:
1902  num_regs = config()->num_simd128_registers();
1903  live_ranges = &data()->fixed_simd128_live_ranges();
1904  break;
1905  default:
1906  break;
1907  }
1908  }
1909 
1910  int offset = spill_mode == SpillMode::kSpillAtDefinition ? 0 : num_regs;
1911 
1912  DCHECK(index < num_regs);
1913  USE(num_regs);
1914  TopLevelLiveRange* result = (*live_ranges)[offset + index];
1915  if (result == nullptr) {
1916  result = data()->NewLiveRange(FixedFPLiveRangeID(offset + index, rep), rep);
1917  DCHECK(result->IsFixed());
1918  result->set_assigned_register(index);
1919  data()->MarkAllocated(rep, index);
1920  if (spill_mode == SpillMode::kSpillDeferred) {
1921  result->set_deferred_fixed();
1922  }
1923  (*live_ranges)[offset + index] = result;
1924  }
1925  return result;
1926 }
1927 
1928 TopLevelLiveRange* LiveRangeBuilder::FixedSIMD128LiveRangeFor(
1929  int index, SpillMode spill_mode) {
1930  DCHECK_EQ(kFPAliasing, AliasingKind::kIndependent);
1931  int num_regs = config()->num_simd128_registers();
1932  ZoneVector<TopLevelLiveRange*>* live_ranges =
1933  &data()->fixed_simd128_live_ranges();
1934  int offset = spill_mode == SpillMode::kSpillAtDefinition ? 0 : num_regs;
1935 
1936  DCHECK(index < num_regs);
1937  USE(num_regs);
1938  TopLevelLiveRange* result = (*live_ranges)[offset + index];
1939  if (result == nullptr) {
1940  result = data()->NewLiveRange(
1941  FixedFPLiveRangeID(offset + index, MachineRepresentation::kSimd128),
1942  MachineRepresentation::kSimd128);
1943  DCHECK(result->IsFixed());
1944  result->set_assigned_register(index);
1945  data()->MarkAllocated(MachineRepresentation::kSimd128, index);
1946  if (spill_mode == SpillMode::kSpillDeferred) {
1947  result->set_deferred_fixed();
1948  }
1949  (*live_ranges)[offset + index] = result;
1950  }
1951  return result;
1952 }
1953 
1954 TopLevelLiveRange* LiveRangeBuilder::LiveRangeFor(InstructionOperand* operand,
1955  SpillMode spill_mode) {
1956  if (operand->IsUnallocated()) {
1957  return data()->GetLiveRangeFor(
1958  UnallocatedOperand::cast(operand)->virtual_register());
1959  } else if (operand->IsConstant()) {
1960  return data()->GetLiveRangeFor(
1961  ConstantOperand::cast(operand)->virtual_register());
1962  } else if (operand->IsRegister()) {
1963  return FixedLiveRangeFor(
1964  LocationOperand::cast(operand)->GetRegister().code(), spill_mode);
1965  } else if (operand->IsFPRegister()) {
1966  LocationOperand* op = LocationOperand::cast(operand);
1967  if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kIndependent &&
1968  op->representation() == MachineRepresentation::kSimd128) {
1969  return FixedSIMD128LiveRangeFor(op->register_code(), spill_mode);
1970  }
1971  return FixedFPLiveRangeFor(op->register_code(), op->representation(),
1972  spill_mode);
1973  } else {
1974  return nullptr;
1975  }
1976 }
1977 
1978 UsePosition* LiveRangeBuilder::NewUsePosition(LifetimePosition pos,
1979  InstructionOperand* operand,
1980  void* hint,
1981  UsePositionHintType hint_type) {
1982  return allocation_zone()->New<UsePosition>(pos, operand, hint, hint_type);
1983 }
1984 
1985 UsePosition* LiveRangeBuilder::Define(LifetimePosition position,
1986  InstructionOperand* operand, void* hint,
1987  UsePositionHintType hint_type,
1988  SpillMode spill_mode) {
1989  TopLevelLiveRange* range = LiveRangeFor(operand, spill_mode);
1990  if (range == nullptr) return nullptr;
1991 
1992  if (range->IsEmpty() || range->Start() > position) {
1993  // Can happen if there is a definition without use.
1994  range->AddUseInterval(position, position.NextStart(), allocation_zone());
1995  range->AddUsePosition(NewUsePosition(position.NextStart()),
1996  allocation_zone());
1997  } else {
1998  range->ShortenTo(position);
1999  }
2000  if (!operand->IsUnallocated()) return nullptr;
2001  UnallocatedOperand* unalloc_operand = UnallocatedOperand::cast(operand);
2002  UsePosition* use_pos =
2003  NewUsePosition(position, unalloc_operand, hint, hint_type);
2004  range->AddUsePosition(use_pos, allocation_zone());
2005  return use_pos;
2006 }
2007 
2008 UsePosition* LiveRangeBuilder::Use(LifetimePosition block_start,
2009  LifetimePosition position,
2010  InstructionOperand* operand, void* hint,
2011  UsePositionHintType hint_type,
2012  SpillMode spill_mode) {
2013  TopLevelLiveRange* range = LiveRangeFor(operand, spill_mode);
2014  if (range == nullptr) return nullptr;
2015  UsePosition* use_pos = nullptr;
2016  if (operand->IsUnallocated()) {
2017  UnallocatedOperand* unalloc_operand = UnallocatedOperand::cast(operand);
2018  use_pos = NewUsePosition(position, unalloc_operand, hint, hint_type);
2019  range->AddUsePosition(use_pos, allocation_zone());
2020  }
2021  range->AddUseInterval(block_start, position, allocation_zone());
2022  return use_pos;
2023 }
2024 
2025 void LiveRangeBuilder::ProcessInstructions(const InstructionBlock* block,
2026  SparseBitVector* live) {
2027  int block_start = block->first_instruction_index();
2028  LifetimePosition block_start_position =
2029  LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(block_start);
2030  bool fixed_float_live_ranges = false;
2031  bool fixed_simd128_live_ranges = false;
2032  if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kCombine) {
2033  int mask = data()->code()->representation_mask();
2034  fixed_float_live_ranges = (mask & kFloat32Bit) != 0;
2035  fixed_simd128_live_ranges = (mask & kSimd128Bit) != 0;
2036  } else if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kIndependent) {
2037  int mask = data()->code()->representation_mask();
2038  fixed_simd128_live_ranges = (mask & kSimd128Bit) != 0;
2039  }
2040  SpillMode spill_mode = SpillModeForBlock(block);
2041 
2042  for (int index = block->last_instruction_index(); index >= block_start;
2043  index--) {
2044  LifetimePosition curr_position =
2045  LifetimePosition::InstructionFromInstructionIndex(index);
2046  Instruction* instr = code()->InstructionAt(index);
2047  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(instr);
2048  DCHECK(curr_position.IsInstructionPosition());
2049  // Process output, inputs, and temps of this instruction.
2050  for (size_t i = 0; i < instr->OutputCount(); i++) {
2051  InstructionOperand* output = instr->OutputAt(i);
2052  if (output->IsUnallocated()) {
2053  // Unsupported.
2054  DCHECK(!UnallocatedOperand::cast(output)->HasSlotPolicy());
2055  int out_vreg = UnallocatedOperand::cast(output)->virtual_register();
2056  live->Remove(out_vreg);
2057  } else if (output->IsConstant()) {
2058  int out_vreg = ConstantOperand::cast(output)->virtual_register();
2059  live->Remove(out_vreg);
2060  }
2061  if (block->IsHandler() && index == block_start && output->IsAllocated() &&
2062  output->IsRegister() &&
2063  AllocatedOperand::cast(output)->GetRegister() ==
2064  v8::internal::kReturnRegister0) {
2065  // The register defined here is blocked from gap start - it is the
2066  // exception value.
2067  // TODO(mtrofin): should we explore an explicit opcode for
2068  // the first instruction in the handler?
2069  Define(LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(index), output,
2070  spill_mode);
2071  } else {
2072  Define(curr_position, output, spill_mode);
2073  }
2074  }
2075 
2076  if (instr->ClobbersRegisters()) {
2077  for (int i = 0; i < config()->num_allocatable_general_registers(); ++i) {
2078  // Create a UseInterval at this instruction for all fixed registers,
2079  // (including the instruction outputs). Adding another UseInterval here
2080  // is OK because AddUseInterval will just merge it with the existing
2081  // one at the end of the range.
2082  int code = config()->GetAllocatableGeneralCode(i);
2083  TopLevelLiveRange* range = FixedLiveRangeFor(code, spill_mode);
2084  range->AddUseInterval(curr_position, curr_position.End(),
2085  allocation_zone());
2086  }
2087  }
2088 
2089  if (instr->ClobbersDoubleRegisters()) {
2090  for (int i = 0; i < config()->num_allocatable_double_registers(); ++i) {
2091  // Add a UseInterval for all DoubleRegisters. See comment above for
2092  // general registers.
2093  int code = config()->GetAllocatableDoubleCode(i);
2094  TopLevelLiveRange* range = FixedFPLiveRangeFor(
2095  code, MachineRepresentation::kFloat64, spill_mode);
2096  range->AddUseInterval(curr_position, curr_position.End(),
2097  allocation_zone());
2098  }
2099  // Clobber fixed float registers on archs with non-simple aliasing.
2100  if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kCombine) {
2101  if (fixed_float_live_ranges) {
2102  for (int i = 0; i < config()->num_allocatable_float_registers();
2103  ++i) {
2104  // Add a UseInterval for all FloatRegisters. See comment above for
2105  // general registers.
2106  int code = config()->GetAllocatableFloatCode(i);
2107  TopLevelLiveRange* range = FixedFPLiveRangeFor(
2108  code, MachineRepresentation::kFloat32, spill_mode);
2109  range->AddUseInterval(curr_position, curr_position.End(),
2110  allocation_zone());
2111  }
2112  }
2113  if (fixed_simd128_live_ranges) {
2114  for (int i = 0; i < config()->num_allocatable_simd128_registers();
2115  ++i) {
2116  int code = config()->GetAllocatableSimd128Code(i);
2117  TopLevelLiveRange* range = FixedFPLiveRangeFor(
2118  code, MachineRepresentation::kSimd128, spill_mode);
2119  range->AddUseInterval(curr_position, curr_position.End(),
2120  allocation_zone());
2121  }
2122  }
2123  } else if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kIndependent) {
2124  if (fixed_simd128_live_ranges) {
2125  for (int i = 0; i < config()->num_allocatable_simd128_registers();
2126  ++i) {
2127  int code = config()->GetAllocatableSimd128Code(i);
2128  TopLevelLiveRange* range =
2129  FixedSIMD128LiveRangeFor(code, spill_mode);
2130  range->AddUseInterval(curr_position, curr_position.End(),
2131  allocation_zone());
2132  }
2133  }
2134  }
2135  }
2136 
2137  for (size_t i = 0; i < instr->InputCount(); i++) {
2138  InstructionOperand* input = instr->InputAt(i);
2139  if (input->IsImmediate()) {
2140  continue; // Ignore immediates.
2141  }
2142  LifetimePosition use_pos;
2143  if (input->IsUnallocated() &&
2144  UnallocatedOperand::cast(input)->IsUsedAtStart()) {
2145  use_pos = curr_position;
2146  } else {
2147  use_pos = curr_position.End();
2148  }
2149 
2150  if (input->IsUnallocated()) {
2151  UnallocatedOperand* unalloc = UnallocatedOperand::cast(input);
2152  int vreg = unalloc->virtual_register();
2153  live->Add(vreg);
2154  if (unalloc->HasSlotPolicy()) {
2155  data()->GetLiveRangeFor(vreg)->register_slot_use(
2156  block->IsDeferred()
2157  ? TopLevelLiveRange::SlotUseKind::kDeferredSlotUse
2158  : TopLevelLiveRange::SlotUseKind::kGeneralSlotUse);
2159  }
2160  }
2161  Use(block_start_position, use_pos, input, spill_mode);
2162  }
2163 
2164  for (size_t i = 0; i < instr->TempCount(); i++) {
2165  InstructionOperand* temp = instr->TempAt(i);
2166  // Unsupported.
2167  DCHECK_IMPLIES(temp->IsUnallocated(),
2168  !UnallocatedOperand::cast(temp)->HasSlotPolicy());
2169  if (instr->ClobbersTemps()) {
2170  if (temp->IsRegister()) continue;
2171  if (temp->IsUnallocated()) {
2172  UnallocatedOperand* temp_unalloc = UnallocatedOperand::cast(temp);
2173  if (temp_unalloc->HasFixedPolicy()) {
2174  continue;
2175  }
2176  }
2177  }
2178  Use(block_start_position, curr_position.End(), temp, spill_mode);
2179  Define(curr_position, temp, spill_mode);
2180  }
2181 
2182  // Process the moves of the instruction's gaps, making their sources live.
2183  const Instruction::GapPosition kPositions[] = {Instruction::END,
2184  Instruction::START};
2185  curr_position = curr_position.PrevStart();
2186  DCHECK(curr_position.IsGapPosition());
2187  for (const Instruction::GapPosition& position : kPositions) {
2188  ParallelMove* move = instr->GetParallelMove(position);
2189  if (move == nullptr) continue;
2190  if (position == Instruction::END) {
2191  curr_position = curr_position.End();
2192  } else {
2193  curr_position = curr_position.Start();
2194  }
2195  for (MoveOperands* cur : *move) {
2196  InstructionOperand& from = cur->source();
2197  InstructionOperand& to = cur->destination();
2198  void* hint = &to;
2199  UsePositionHintType hint_type = UsePosition::HintTypeForOperand(to);
2200  UsePosition* to_use = nullptr;
2201  int phi_vreg = -1;
2202  if (to.IsUnallocated()) {
2203  int to_vreg = UnallocatedOperand::cast(to).virtual_register();
2204  TopLevelLiveRange* to_range = data()->GetLiveRangeFor(to_vreg);
2205  if (to_range->is_phi()) {
2206  phi_vreg = to_vreg;
2207  if (to_range->is_non_loop_phi()) {
2208  hint = to_range->current_hint_position();
2209  hint_type = hint == nullptr ? UsePositionHintType::kNone
2210  : UsePositionHintType::kUsePos;
2211  } else {
2212  hint_type = UsePositionHintType::kPhi;
2213  hint = data()->GetPhiMapValueFor(to_vreg);
2214  }
2215  } else {
2216  if (live->Contains(to_vreg)) {
2217  to_use =
2218  Define(curr_position, &to, &from,
2219  UsePosition::HintTypeForOperand(from), spill_mode);
2220  live->Remove(to_vreg);
2221  } else {
2222  cur->Eliminate();
2223  continue;
2224  }
2225  }
2226  } else {
2227  Define(curr_position, &to, spill_mode);
2228  }
2229  UsePosition* from_use = Use(block_start_position, curr_position, &from,
2230  hint, hint_type, spill_mode);
2231  // Mark range live.
2232  if (from.IsUnallocated()) {
2233  live->Add(UnallocatedOperand::cast(from).virtual_register());
2234  }
2235  // When the value is moved to a register to meet input constraints,
2236  // we should consider this value use similar as a register use in the
2237  // backward spilling heuristics, even though this value use is not
2238  // register benefical at the AllocateBlockedReg stage.
2239  if (to.IsAnyRegister() ||
2240  (to.IsUnallocated() &&
2241  UnallocatedOperand::cast(&to)->HasRegisterPolicy())) {
2242  from_use->set_spill_detrimental();
2243  }
2244  // Resolve use position hints just created.
2245  if (to_use != nullptr && from_use != nullptr) {
2246  to_use->ResolveHint(from_use);
2247  from_use->ResolveHint(to_use);
2248  }
2249  DCHECK_IMPLIES(to_use != nullptr, to_use->IsResolved());
2250  DCHECK_IMPLIES(from_use != nullptr, from_use->IsResolved());
2251  // Potentially resolve phi hint.
2252  if (phi_vreg != -1) ResolvePhiHint(&from, from_use);
2253  }
2254  }
2255  }
2256 }
2257 
2258 void LiveRangeBuilder::ProcessPhis(const InstructionBlock* block,
2259  SparseBitVector* live) {
2260  for (PhiInstruction* phi : block->phis()) {
2261  // The live range interval already ends at the first instruction of the
2262  // block.
2263  int phi_vreg = phi->virtual_register();
2264  live->Remove(phi_vreg);
2265  // Select a hint from a predecessor block that precedes this block in the
2266  // rpo order. In order of priority:
2267  // - Avoid hints from deferred blocks.
2268  // - Prefer hints from allocated (or explicit) operands.
2269  // - Prefer hints from empty blocks (containing just parallel moves and a
2270  // jump). In these cases, if we can elide the moves, the jump threader
2271  // is likely to be able to elide the jump.
2272  // The enforcement of hinting in rpo order is required because hint
2273  // resolution that happens later in the compiler pipeline visits
2274  // instructions in reverse rpo order, relying on the fact that phis are
2275  // encountered before their hints.
2276  InstructionOperand* hint = nullptr;
2277  int hint_preference = 0;
2278 
2279  // The cost of hinting increases with the number of predecessors. At the
2280  // same time, the typical benefit decreases, since this hinting only
2281  // optimises the execution path through one predecessor. A limit of 2 is
2282  // sufficient to hit the common if/else pattern.
2283  int predecessor_limit = 2;
2284 
2285  for (RpoNumber predecessor : block->predecessors()) {
2286  const InstructionBlock* predecessor_block =
2287  code()->InstructionBlockAt(predecessor);
2288  DCHECK_EQ(predecessor_block->rpo_number(), predecessor);
2289 
2290  // Only take hints from earlier rpo numbers.
2291  if (predecessor >= block->rpo_number()) continue;
2292 
2293  // Look up the predecessor instruction.
2294  const Instruction* predecessor_instr =
2295  GetLastInstruction(code(), predecessor_block);
2296  InstructionOperand* predecessor_hint = nullptr;
2297  // Phis are assigned in the END position of the last instruction in each
2298  // predecessor block.
2299  for (MoveOperands* move :
2300  *predecessor_instr->GetParallelMove(Instruction::END)) {
2301  InstructionOperand& to = move->destination();
2302  if (to.IsUnallocated() &&
2303  UnallocatedOperand::cast(to).virtual_register() == phi_vreg) {
2304  predecessor_hint = &move->source();
2305  break;
2306  }
2307  }
2308  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(predecessor_hint);
2309 
2310  // For each predecessor, generate a score according to the priorities
2311  // described above, and pick the best one. Flags in higher-order bits have
2312  // a higher priority than those in lower-order bits.
2313  int predecessor_hint_preference = 0;
2314  const int kNotDeferredBlockPreference = (1 << 2);
2315  const int kMoveIsAllocatedPreference = (1 << 1);
2316  const int kBlockIsEmptyPreference = (1 << 0);
2317 
2318  // - Avoid hints from deferred blocks.
2319  if (!predecessor_block->IsDeferred()) {
2320  predecessor_hint_preference |= kNotDeferredBlockPreference;
2321  }
2322 
2323  // - Prefer hints from allocated operands.
2324  //
2325  // Already-allocated operands are typically assigned using the parallel
2326  // moves on the last instruction. For example:
2327  //
2328  // gap (v101 = [x0|R|w32]) (v100 = v101)
2329  // ArchJmp
2330  // ...
2331  // phi: v100 = v101 v102
2332  //
2333  // We have already found the END move, so look for a matching START move
2334  // from an allocated operand.
2335  //
2336  // Note that we cannot simply look up data()->live_ranges()[vreg] here
2337  // because the live ranges are still being built when this function is
2338  // called.
2339  // TODO(v8): Find a way to separate hinting from live range analysis in
2340  // BuildLiveRanges so that we can use the O(1) live-range look-up.
2341  auto moves = predecessor_instr->GetParallelMove(Instruction::START);
2342  if (moves != nullptr) {
2343  for (MoveOperands* move : *moves) {
2344  InstructionOperand& to = move->destination();
2345  if (predecessor_hint->Equals(to)) {
2346  if (move->source().IsAllocated()) {
2347  predecessor_hint_preference |= kMoveIsAllocatedPreference;
2348  }
2349  break;
2350  }
2351  }
2352  }
2353 
2354  // - Prefer hints from empty blocks.
2355  if (predecessor_block->last_instruction_index() ==
2356  predecessor_block->first_instruction_index()) {
2357  predecessor_hint_preference |= kBlockIsEmptyPreference;
2358  }
2359 
2360  if ((hint == nullptr) ||
2361  (predecessor_hint_preference > hint_preference)) {
2362  // Take the hint from this predecessor.
2363  hint = predecessor_hint;
2364  hint_preference = predecessor_hint_preference;
2365  }
2366 
2367  if (--predecessor_limit <= 0) break;
2368  }
2369  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(hint);
2370 
2371  LifetimePosition block_start = LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(
2372  block->first_instruction_index());
2373  UsePosition* use_pos = Define(block_start, &phi->output(), hint,
2374  UsePosition::HintTypeForOperand(*hint),
2375  SpillModeForBlock(block));
2376  MapPhiHint(hint, use_pos);
2377  }
2378 }
2379 
2380 void LiveRangeBuilder::ProcessLoopHeader(const InstructionBlock* block,
2381  SparseBitVector* live) {
2382  DCHECK(block->IsLoopHeader());
2383  // Add a live range stretching from the first loop instruction to the last
2384  // for each value live on entry to the header.
2385  LifetimePosition start = LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(
2386  block->first_instruction_index());
2387  LifetimePosition end = LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(
2388  code()->LastLoopInstructionIndex(block))
2389  .NextFullStart();
2390  for (int operand_index : *live) {
2391  TopLevelLiveRange* range = data()->GetLiveRangeFor(operand_index);
2392  range->EnsureInterval(start, end, allocation_zone());
2393  }
2394  // Insert all values into the live in sets of all blocks in the loop.
2395  for (int i = block->rpo_number().ToInt() + 1; i < block->loop_end().ToInt();
2396  ++i) {
2397  live_in_sets()[i]->Union(*live);
2398  }
2399 }
2400 
2401 void LiveRangeBuilder::BuildLiveRanges() {
2402  // Process the blocks in reverse order.
2403  for (int block_id = code()->InstructionBlockCount() - 1; block_id >= 0;
2404  --block_id) {
2405  data_->tick_counter()->TickAndMaybeEnterSafepoint();
2406  InstructionBlock* block =
2407  code()->InstructionBlockAt(RpoNumber::FromInt(block_id));
2408  SparseBitVector* live = ComputeLiveOut(block, data());
2409  // Initially consider all live_out values live for the entire block. We
2410  // will shorten these intervals if necessary.
2411  AddInitialIntervals(block, live);
2412  // Process the instructions in reverse order, generating and killing
2413  // live values.
2414  ProcessInstructions(block, live);
2415  // All phi output operands are killed by this block.
2416  ProcessPhis(block, live);
2417  // Now live is live_in for this block except not including values live
2418  // out on backward successor edges.
2419  if (block->IsLoopHeader()) ProcessLoopHeader(block, live);
2420  live_in_sets()[block_id] = live;
2421  }
2422  // Postprocess the ranges.
2423  const size_t live_ranges_size = data()->live_ranges().size();
2424  for (TopLevelLiveRange* range : data()->live_ranges()) {
2425  data_->tick_counter()->TickAndMaybeEnterSafepoint();
2426  CHECK_EQ(live_ranges_size,
2427  data()->live_ranges().size()); // TODO(neis): crbug.com/831822
2428  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(range);
2429  // Give slots to all ranges with a non fixed slot use.
2430  if (range->has_slot_use() && range->HasNoSpillType()) {
2431  SpillMode spill_mode =
2432  range->slot_use_kind() ==
2433  TopLevelLiveRange::SlotUseKind::kDeferredSlotUse
2434  ? SpillMode::kSpillDeferred
2435  : SpillMode::kSpillAtDefinition;
2436  data()->AssignSpillRangeToLiveRange(range, spill_mode);
2437  }
2438  // TODO(bmeurer): This is a horrible hack to make sure that for constant
2439  // live ranges, every use requires the constant to be in a register.
2440  // Without this hack, all uses with "any" policy would get the constant
2441  // operand assigned.
2442  if (range->HasSpillOperand() && range->GetSpillOperand()->IsConstant()) {
2443  for (UsePosition* pos : range->positions()) {
2444  if (pos->type() == UsePositionType::kRequiresSlot ||
2445  pos->type() == UsePositionType::kRegisterOrSlotOrConstant) {
2446  continue;
2447  }
2448  UsePositionType new_type = UsePositionType::kRegisterOrSlot;
2449  // Can't mark phis as needing a register.
2450  if (!pos->pos().IsGapPosition()) {
2451  new_type = UsePositionType::kRequiresRegister;
2452  }
2453  pos->set_type(new_type, true);
2454  }
2455  }
2456  range->ResetCurrentHintPosition();
2457  }
2458  for (auto preassigned : data()->preassigned_slot_ranges()) {
2459  TopLevelLiveRange* range = preassigned.first;
2460  int slot_id = preassigned.second;
2461  SpillRange* spill = range->HasSpillRange()
2462  ? range->GetSpillRange()
2463  : data()->AssignSpillRangeToLiveRange(
2464  range, SpillMode::kSpillAtDefinition);
2465  spill->set_assigned_slot(slot_id);
2466  }
2467 #ifdef DEBUG
2468  Verify();
2469 #endif
2470 }
2471 
2472 void LiveRangeBuilder::MapPhiHint(InstructionOperand* operand,
2473  UsePosition* use_pos) {
2474  DCHECK(!use_pos->IsResolved());
2475  auto res = phi_hints_.insert(std::make_pair(operand, use_pos));
2476  DCHECK(res.second);
2477  USE(res);
2478 }
2479 
2480 void LiveRangeBuilder::ResolvePhiHint(InstructionOperand* operand,
2481  UsePosition* use_pos) {
2482  auto it = phi_hints_.find(operand);
2483  if (it == phi_hints_.end()) return;
2484  DCHECK(!it->second->IsResolved());
2485  it->second->ResolveHint(use_pos);
2486 }
2487 
2488 #ifdef DEBUG
2489 void LiveRangeBuilder::Verify() const {
2490  for (auto& hint : phi_hints_) {
2491  DCHECK(hint.second->IsResolved());
2492  }
2493  for (TopLevelLiveRange* current : data()->live_ranges()) {
2494  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(current);
2495  if (!current->IsEmpty()) {
2496  // New LiveRanges should not be split.
2497  DCHECK_NULL(current->next());
2498  // General integrity check.
2499  current->Verify();
2500  if (current->intervals().size() < 2) continue;
2501 
2502  // Consecutive intervals should not end and start in the same block,
2503  // otherwise the intervals should have been joined, because the
2504  // variable is live throughout that block.
2505  UseIntervalVector::const_iterator interval = current->intervals().begin();
2506  UseIntervalVector::const_iterator next_interval = interval + 1;
2507  DCHECK(NextIntervalStartsInDifferentBlocks(*interval, *next_interval));
2508 
2509  for (++interval; interval != current->intervals().end(); ++interval) {
2510  // Except for the first interval, the other intevals must start at
2511  // a block boundary, otherwise data wouldn't flow to them.
2512  // You might trigger this CHECK if your SSA is not valid. For instance,
2513  // if the inputs of a Phi node are in the wrong order.
2514  DCHECK(IntervalStartsAtBlockBoundary(*interval));
2515  // The last instruction of the predecessors of the block the interval
2516  // starts must be covered by the range.
2517  DCHECK(IntervalPredecessorsCoveredByRange(*interval, current));
2518  next_interval = interval + 1;
2519  if (next_interval != current->intervals().end()) {
2520  // Check the consecutive intervals property, except for the last
2521  // interval, where it doesn't apply.
2522  DCHECK(
2523  NextIntervalStartsInDifferentBlocks(*interval, *next_interval));
2524  }
2525  }
2526  }
2527  }
2528 }
2529 
2530 bool LiveRangeBuilder::IntervalStartsAtBlockBoundary(
2531  UseInterval interval) const {
2532  LifetimePosition start = interval.start();
2533  if (!start.IsFullStart()) return false;
2534  int instruction_index = start.ToInstructionIndex();
2535  const InstructionBlock* block =
2536  data()->code()->GetInstructionBlock(instruction_index);
2537  return block->first_instruction_index() == instruction_index;
2538 }
2539 
2540 bool LiveRangeBuilder::IntervalPredecessorsCoveredByRange(
2541  UseInterval interval, TopLevelLiveRange* range) const {
2542  LifetimePosition start = interval.start();
2543  int instruction_index = start.ToInstructionIndex();
2544  const InstructionBlock* block =
2545  data()->code()->GetInstructionBlock(instruction_index);
2546  for (RpoNumber pred_index : block->predecessors()) {
2547  const InstructionBlock* predecessor =
2548  data()->code()->InstructionBlockAt(pred_index);
2549  LifetimePosition last_pos = LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(
2550  predecessor->last_instruction_index());
2551  last_pos = last_pos.NextStart().End();
2552  if (!range->Covers(last_pos)) return false;
2553  }
2554  return true;
2555 }
2556 
2557 bool LiveRangeBuilder::NextIntervalStartsInDifferentBlocks(
2558  UseInterval interval, UseInterval next) const {
2559  LifetimePosition end = interval.end();
2560  LifetimePosition next_start = next.start();
2561  // Since end is not covered, but the previous position is, move back a
2562  // position
2563  end = end.IsStart() ? end.PrevStart().End() : end.Start();
2564  int last_covered_index = end.ToInstructionIndex();
2565  const InstructionBlock* block =
2566  data()->code()->GetInstructionBlock(last_covered_index);
2567  const InstructionBlock* next_block =
2568  data()->code()->GetInstructionBlock(next_start.ToInstructionIndex());
2569  return block->rpo_number() < next_block->rpo_number();
2570 }
2571 #endif
2572 
2573 void BundleBuilder::BuildBundles() {
2574  TRACE("Build bundles\n");
2575  // Process the blocks in reverse order.
2576  for (int block_id = code()->InstructionBlockCount() - 1; block_id >= 0;
2577  --block_id) {
2578  InstructionBlock* block =
2579  code()->InstructionBlockAt(RpoNumber::FromInt(block_id));
2580  TRACE("Block B%d\n", block_id);
2581  for (auto phi : block->phis()) {
2582  TopLevelLiveRange* out_range =
2583  data()->GetLiveRangeFor(phi->virtual_register());
2584  LiveRangeBundle* out = out_range->get_bundle();
2585  if (out == nullptr) {
2586  out = data()->allocation_zone()->New<LiveRangeBundle>(
2587  data()->allocation_zone(), next_bundle_id_++);
2588  out->TryAddRange(out_range);
2589  }
2590  TRACE("Processing phi for v%d with %d:%d\n", phi->virtual_register(),
2591  out_range->TopLevel()->vreg(), out_range->relative_id());
2592  bool phi_interferes_with_backedge_input = false;
2593  for (auto input : phi->operands()) {
2594  TopLevelLiveRange* input_range = data()->GetLiveRangeFor(input);
2595  TRACE("Input value v%d with range %d:%d\n", input,
2596  input_range->TopLevel()->vreg(), input_range->relative_id());
2597  LiveRangeBundle* input_bundle = input_range->get_bundle();
2598  if (input_bundle != nullptr) {
2599  TRACE("Merge\n");
2600  LiveRangeBundle* merged =
2601  LiveRangeBundle::TryMerge(out, input_bundle);
2602  if (merged != nullptr) {
2603  DCHECK_EQ(out_range->get_bundle(), merged);
2604  DCHECK_EQ(input_range->get_bundle(), merged);
2605  out = merged;
2606  TRACE("Merged %d and %d to %d\n", phi->virtual_register(), input,
2607  out->id());
2608  } else if (input_range->Start() > out_range->Start()) {
2609  // We are only interested in values defined after the phi, because
2610  // those are values that will go over a back-edge.
2611  phi_interferes_with_backedge_input = true;
2612  }
2613  } else {
2614  TRACE("Add\n");
2615  if (out->TryAddRange(input_range)) {
2616  TRACE("Added %d and %d to %d\n", phi->virtual_register(), input,
2617  out->id());
2618  } else if (input_range->Start() > out_range->Start()) {
2619  // We are only interested in values defined after the phi, because
2620  // those are values that will go over a back-edge.
2621  phi_interferes_with_backedge_input = true;
2622  }
2623  }
2624  }
2625  // Spilling the phi at the loop header is not beneficial if there is
2626  // a back-edge with an input for the phi that interferes with the phi's
2627  // value, because in case that input gets spilled it might introduce
2628  // a stack-to-stack move at the back-edge.
2629  if (phi_interferes_with_backedge_input)
2630  out_range->TopLevel()->set_spilling_at_loop_header_not_beneficial();
2631  }
2632  TRACE("Done block B%d\n", block_id);
2633  }
2634 }
2635 
2636 bool LiveRangeBundle::TryAddRange(TopLevelLiveRange* range) {
2637  DCHECK_NULL(range->get_bundle());
2638  // We may only add a new live range if its use intervals do not
2639  // overlap with existing intervals in the bundle.
2640  if (AreUseIntervalsIntersecting(this->intervals_, range->intervals()))
2641  return false;
2642  AddRange(range);
2643  return true;
2644 }
2645 
2646 void LiveRangeBundle::AddRange(TopLevelLiveRange* range) {
2647  TopLevelLiveRange** range_insert_it = std::lower_bound(
2648  ranges_.begin(), ranges_.end(), range, LiveRangeOrdering());
2649  DCHECK_IMPLIES(range_insert_it != ranges_.end(), *range_insert_it != range);
2650  // TODO(dlehmann): We might save some memory by using
2651  // `DoubleEndedSplitVector::insert<kFront>()` here: Since we add ranges
2652  // mostly backwards, ranges with an earlier `Start()` are inserted mostly
2653  // at the front.
2654  ranges_.insert(range_insert_it, 1, range);
2655  range->set_bundle(this);
2656 
2657  // We also tried `std::merge`ing the sorted vectors of `intervals_` directly,
2658  // but it turns out the (always happening) copies are more expensive
2659  // than the (apparently seldom) copies due to insertion in the middle.
2660  for (UseInterval interval : range->intervals()) {
2661  UseInterval* interval_insert_it =
2662  std::lower_bound(intervals_.begin(), intervals_.end(), interval);
2663  DCHECK_IMPLIES(interval_insert_it != intervals_.end(),
2664  *interval_insert_it != interval);
2665  intervals_.insert(interval_insert_it, 1, interval);
2666  }
2667 }
2668 
2669 LiveRangeBundle* LiveRangeBundle::TryMerge(LiveRangeBundle* lhs,
2670  LiveRangeBundle* rhs) {
2671  if (rhs == lhs) return lhs;
2672 
2673  if (auto found =
2674  AreUseIntervalsIntersecting(lhs->intervals_, rhs->intervals_)) {
2675  auto [interval1, interval2] = *found;
2676  TRACE("No merge %d:%d %d:%d\n", interval1.start().value(),
2677  interval1.end().value(), interval2.start().value(),
2678  interval2.end().value());
2679  return nullptr;
2680  }
2681  // Uses are disjoint, merging is possible.
2682 
2683  // Merge the smaller bundle into the bigger.
2684  if (lhs->intervals_.size() < rhs->intervals_.size()) {
2685  std::swap(lhs, rhs);
2686  }
2687  for (TopLevelLiveRange* range : rhs->ranges_) {
2688  lhs->AddRange(range);
2689  }
2690 
2691  rhs->ranges_.clear();
2692  rhs->intervals_.clear();
2693 
2694  return lhs;
2695 }
2696 
2697 void LiveRangeBundle::MergeSpillRangesAndClear() {
2698  DCHECK_IMPLIES(ranges_.empty(), intervals_.empty());
2699  SpillRange* target = nullptr;
2700  for (auto range : ranges_) {
2701  if (range->TopLevel()->HasSpillRange()) {
2702  SpillRange* current = range->TopLevel()->GetSpillRange();
2703  if (target == nullptr) {
2704  target = current;
2705  } else if (target != current) {
2706  target->TryMerge(current);
2707  }
2708  }
2709  }
2710  // Clear the fields so that we don't try to merge the spill ranges again when
2711  // we hit the same bundle from a different LiveRange in AssignSpillSlots.
2712  // LiveRangeBundles are not used after this.
2713  ranges_.clear();
2714  intervals_.clear();
2715 }

2717 RegisterAllocator::RegisterAllocator(RegisterAllocationData* data,
2718  RegisterKind kind)
2719  : data_(data),
2720  mode_(kind),
2721  num_registers_(GetRegisterCount(data->config(), kind)),
2722  num_allocatable_registers_(
2723  GetAllocatableRegisterCount(data->config(), kind)),
2724  allocatable_register_codes_(
2725  GetAllocatableRegisterCodes(data->config(), kind)),
2726  check_fp_aliasing_(false) {
2727  if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kCombine && kind == RegisterKind::kDouble) {
2728  check_fp_aliasing_ = (data->code()->representation_mask() &
2729  (kFloat32Bit | kSimd128Bit)) != 0;
2730  }
2731 }

2733 LifetimePosition RegisterAllocator::GetSplitPositionForInstruction(
2734  const LiveRange* range, int instruction_index) {
2735  LifetimePosition ret = LifetimePosition::Invalid();
2736 
2737  ret = LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(instruction_index);
2738  if (range->Start() >= ret || ret >= range->End()) {
2739  return LifetimePosition::Invalid();
2740  }
2741  return ret;
2742 }
2743 
2744 void RegisterAllocator::SplitAndSpillRangesDefinedByMemoryOperand() {
2745  size_t initial_range_count = data()->live_ranges().size();
2746  for (size_t i = 0; i < initial_range_count; ++i) {
2747  CHECK_EQ(initial_range_count,
2748  data()->live_ranges().size()); // TODO(neis): crbug.com/831822
2749  TopLevelLiveRange* range = data()->live_ranges()[i];
2750  if (!CanProcessRange(range)) continue;
2751  // Only assume defined by memory operand if we are guaranteed to spill it or
2752  // it has a spill operand.
2753  if (range->HasNoSpillType() ||
2754  (range->HasSpillRange() && !range->has_non_deferred_slot_use())) {
2755  continue;
2756  }
2757  LifetimePosition start = range->Start();
2758  TRACE("Live range %d:%d is defined by a spill operand.\n",
2759  range->TopLevel()->vreg(), range->relative_id());
2760  LifetimePosition next_pos = start;
2761  if (next_pos.IsGapPosition()) {
2762  next_pos = next_pos.NextStart();
2763  }
2764 
2765  UsePosition* pos = range->NextUsePositionRegisterIsBeneficial(next_pos);
2766  // If the range already has a spill operand and it doesn't need a
2767  // register immediately, split it and spill the first part of the range.
2768  if (pos == nullptr) {
2769  Spill(range, SpillMode::kSpillAtDefinition);
2770  } else if (pos->pos() > range->Start().NextStart()) {
2771  // Do not spill live range eagerly if use position that can benefit from
2772  // the register is too close to the start of live range.
2773  LifetimePosition split_pos = GetSplitPositionForInstruction(
2774  range, pos->pos().ToInstructionIndex());
2775  // There is no place to split, so we can't split and spill.
2776  if (!split_pos.IsValid()) continue;
2777 
2778  split_pos =
2779  FindOptimalSplitPos(range->Start().NextFullStart(), split_pos);
2780 
2781  SplitRangeAt(range, split_pos);
2782  Spill(range, SpillMode::kSpillAtDefinition);
2783  }
2784  }
2785 }
2786 
2787 LiveRange* RegisterAllocator::SplitRangeAt(LiveRange* range,
2788  LifetimePosition pos) {
2789  DCHECK(!range->TopLevel()->IsFixed());
2790  TRACE("Splitting live range %d:%d at %d\n", range->TopLevel()->vreg(),
2791  range->relative_id(), pos.value());
2792 
2793  if (pos <= range->Start()) return range;
2794 
2795  // We can't properly connect liveranges if splitting occurred at the end
2796  // a block.
2797  DCHECK(pos.IsStart() || pos.IsGapPosition() ||
2798  (GetInstructionBlock(code(), pos)->last_instruction_index() !=
2799  pos.ToInstructionIndex()));
2800 
2801  LiveRange* result = range->SplitAt(pos, allocation_zone());
2802  return result;
2803 }
2804 
2805 LiveRange* RegisterAllocator::SplitBetween(LiveRange* range,
2806  LifetimePosition start,
2807  LifetimePosition end) {
2808  DCHECK(!range->TopLevel()->IsFixed());
2809  TRACE("Splitting live range %d:%d in position between [%d, %d]\n",
2810  range->TopLevel()->vreg(), range->relative_id(), start.value(),
2811  end.value());
2812 
2813  LifetimePosition split_pos = FindOptimalSplitPos(start, end);
2814  DCHECK(split_pos >= start);
2815  return SplitRangeAt(range, split_pos);
2816 }
2817 
2818 LifetimePosition RegisterAllocator::FindOptimalSplitPos(LifetimePosition start,
2819  LifetimePosition end) {
2820  int start_instr = start.ToInstructionIndex();
2821  int end_instr = end.ToInstructionIndex();
2822  DCHECK_LE(start_instr, end_instr);
2823 
2824  // We have no choice
2825  if (start_instr == end_instr) return end;
2826 
2827  const InstructionBlock* start_block = GetInstructionBlock(code(), start);
2828  const InstructionBlock* end_block = GetInstructionBlock(code(), end);
2829 
2830  if (end_block == start_block) {
2831  // The interval is split in the same basic block. Split at the latest
2832  // possible position.
2833  return end;
2834  }
2835 
2836  const InstructionBlock* block = end_block;
2837  // Find header of outermost loop.
2838  do {
2839  const InstructionBlock* loop = GetContainingLoop(code(), block);
2840  if (loop == nullptr ||
2841  loop->rpo_number().ToInt() <= start_block->rpo_number().ToInt()) {
2842  // No more loops or loop starts before the lifetime start.
2843  break;
2844  }
2845  block = loop;
2846  } while (true);
2847 
2848  // We did not find any suitable outer loop. Split at the latest possible
2849  // position unless end_block is a loop header itself.
2850  if (block == end_block && !end_block->IsLoopHeader()) return end;
2851 
2852  return LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(
2853  block->first_instruction_index());
2854 }
2855 
2856 LifetimePosition RegisterAllocator::FindOptimalSpillingPos(
2857  LiveRange* range, LifetimePosition pos, SpillMode spill_mode,
2858  LiveRange** begin_spill_out) {
2859  *begin_spill_out = range;
2860  // TODO(herhut): Be more clever here as long as we do not move pos out of
2861  // deferred code.
2862  if (spill_mode == SpillMode::kSpillDeferred) return pos;
2863  const InstructionBlock* block = GetInstructionBlock(code(), pos.Start());
2864  const InstructionBlock* loop_header =
2865  block->IsLoopHeader() ? block : GetContainingLoop(code(), block);
2866  if (loop_header == nullptr) return pos;
2867 
2868  while (loop_header != nullptr) {
2869  // We are going to spill live range inside the loop.
2870  // If possible try to move spilling position backwards to loop header.
2871  // This will reduce number of memory moves on the back edge.
2872  LifetimePosition loop_start = LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(
2873  loop_header->first_instruction_index());
2874  // Stop if we moved to a loop header before the value is defined or
2875  // at the define position that is not beneficial to spill.
2876  if (range->TopLevel()->Start() > loop_start ||
2877  (range->TopLevel()->Start() == loop_start &&
2878  range->TopLevel()->SpillAtLoopHeaderNotBeneficial()))
2879  return pos;
2880 
2881  LiveRange* live_at_header = range->TopLevel()->GetChildCovers(loop_start);
2882 
2883  if (live_at_header != nullptr && !live_at_header->spilled()) {
2884  for (const LiveRange* check_use = live_at_header;
2885  check_use != nullptr && check_use->Start() < pos;
2886  check_use = check_use->next()) {
2887  // If we find a use for which spilling is detrimental, don't spill
2888  // at the loop header
2889  UsePosition* next_use =
2890  check_use->NextUsePositionSpillDetrimental(loop_start);
2891  // UsePosition at the end of a UseInterval may
2892  // have the same value as the start of next range.
2893  if (next_use != nullptr && next_use->pos() <= pos) {
2894  return pos;
2895  }
2896  }
2897  // No register beneficial use inside the loop before the pos.
2898  *begin_spill_out = live_at_header;
2899  pos = loop_start;
2900  }
2901 
2902  // Try hoisting out to an outer loop.
2903  loop_header = GetContainingLoop(code(), loop_header);
2904  }
2905  return pos;
2906 }
2907 
2908 void RegisterAllocator::Spill(LiveRange* range, SpillMode spill_mode) {
2909  DCHECK(!range->spilled());
2910  DCHECK(spill_mode == SpillMode::kSpillAtDefinition ||
2911  GetInstructionBlock(code(), range->Start())->IsDeferred());
2912  TopLevelLiveRange* first = range->TopLevel();
2913  TRACE("Spilling live range %d:%d mode %d\n", first->vreg(),
2914  range->relative_id(), spill_mode);
2915 
2916  TRACE("Starting spill type is %d\n", static_cast<int>(first->spill_type()));
2917  if (first->HasNoSpillType()) {
2918  TRACE("New spill range needed\n");
2919  data()->AssignSpillRangeToLiveRange(first, spill_mode);
2920  }
2921  // Upgrade the spillmode, in case this was only spilled in deferred code so
2922  // far.
2923  if ((spill_mode == SpillMode::kSpillAtDefinition) &&
2924  (first->spill_type() ==
2925  TopLevelLiveRange::SpillType::kDeferredSpillRange)) {
2926  TRACE("Upgrading\n");
2927  first->set_spill_type(TopLevelLiveRange::SpillType::kSpillRange);
2928  }
2929  TRACE("Final spill type is %d\n", static_cast<int>(first->spill_type()));
2930  range->Spill();
2931 }
2932 
2933 const char* RegisterAllocator::RegisterName(int register_code) const {
2934  if (register_code == kUnassignedRegister) return "unassigned";
2935  switch (mode()) {
2936  case RegisterKind::kGeneral:
2937  return i::RegisterName(Register::from_code(register_code));
2938  case RegisterKind::kDouble:
2939  return i::RegisterName(DoubleRegister::from_code(register_code));
2940  case RegisterKind::kSimd128:
2941  return i::RegisterName(Simd128Register::from_code(register_code));
2942  }
2943 }

2945 LinearScanAllocator::LinearScanAllocator(RegisterAllocationData* data,
2946  RegisterKind kind, Zone* local_zone)
2947  : RegisterAllocator(data, kind),
2948  unhandled_live_ranges_(local_zone),
2949  active_live_ranges_(local_zone),
2950  inactive_live_ranges_(num_registers(), InactiveLiveRangeQueue(local_zone),
2951  local_zone),
2952  next_active_ranges_change_(LifetimePosition::Invalid()),
2953  next_inactive_ranges_change_(LifetimePosition::Invalid()) {
2954  active_live_ranges().reserve(8);
2955 }
2956 
2957 void LinearScanAllocator::MaybeSpillPreviousRanges(LiveRange* begin_range,
2958  LifetimePosition begin_pos,
2959  LiveRange* end_range) {
2960  // Spill begin_range after begin_pos, then spill every live range of this
2961  // virtual register until but excluding end_range.
2962  DCHECK(begin_range->Covers(begin_pos));
2963  DCHECK_EQ(begin_range->TopLevel(), end_range->TopLevel());
2964 
2965  if (begin_range != end_range) {
2966  DCHECK_LE(begin_range->End(), end_range->Start());
2967  if (!begin_range->spilled()) {
2968  SpillAfter(begin_range, begin_pos, SpillMode::kSpillAtDefinition);
2969  }
2970  for (LiveRange* range = begin_range->next(); range != end_range;
2971  range = range->next()) {
2972  if (!range->spilled()) {
2973  range->Spill();
2974  }
2975  }
2976  }
2977 }
2978 
2979 void LinearScanAllocator::MaybeUndoPreviousSplit(LiveRange* range, Zone* zone) {
2980  if (range->next() != nullptr && range->next()->ShouldRecombine()) {
2981  LiveRange* to_remove = range->next();
2982  TRACE("Recombining %d:%d with %d\n", range->TopLevel()->vreg(),
2983  range->relative_id(), to_remove->relative_id());
2984 
2985  // Remove the range from unhandled, as attaching it will change its
2986  // state and hence ordering in the unhandled set.
2987  auto removed_cnt = unhandled_live_ranges().erase(to_remove);
2988  DCHECK_EQ(removed_cnt, 1);
2989  USE(removed_cnt);
2990 
2991  range->AttachToNext(zone);
2992  } else if (range->next() != nullptr) {
2993  TRACE("No recombine for %d:%d to %d\n", range->TopLevel()->vreg(),
2994  range->relative_id(), range->next()->relative_id());
2995  }
2996 }
2997 
2998 void LinearScanAllocator::SpillNotLiveRanges(RangeRegisterSmallMap& to_be_live,
2999  LifetimePosition position,
3000  SpillMode spill_mode) {
3001  for (auto it = active_live_ranges().begin();
3002  it != active_live_ranges().end();) {
3003  LiveRange* active_range = *it;
3004  TopLevelLiveRange* toplevel = (*it)->TopLevel();
3005  auto found = to_be_live.find(toplevel);
3006  if (found == to_be_live.end()) {
3007  // Is not contained in {to_be_live}, spill it.
3008  // Fixed registers are exempt from this. They might have been
3009  // added from inactive at the block boundary but we know that
3010  // they cannot conflict as they are built before register
3011  // allocation starts. It would be algorithmically fine to split
3012  // them and reschedule but the code does not allow to do this.
3013  if (toplevel->IsFixed()) {
3014  TRACE("Keeping reactivated fixed range for %s\n",
3015  RegisterName(toplevel->assigned_register()));
3016  ++it;
3017  } else {
3018  // When spilling a previously spilled/reloaded range, we add back the
3019  // tail that we might have split off when we reloaded/spilled it
3020  // previously. Otherwise we might keep generating small split-offs.
3021  MaybeUndoPreviousSplit(active_range, allocation_zone());
3022  TRACE("Putting back %d:%d\n", toplevel->vreg(),
3023  active_range->relative_id());
3024  LiveRange* split = SplitRangeAt(active_range, position);
3025  DCHECK_NE(split, active_range);
3026 
3027  // Make sure we revisit this range once it has a use that requires
3028  // a register.
3029  UsePosition* next_use = split->NextRegisterPosition(position);
3030  if (next_use != nullptr) {
3031  // Move to the start of the gap before use so that we have a space
3032  // to perform the potential reload. Otherwise, do not spill but add
3033  // to unhandled for reallocation.
3034  LifetimePosition revisit_at = next_use->pos().FullStart();
3035  TRACE("Next use at %d\n", revisit_at.value());
3036  if (!data()->IsBlockBoundary(revisit_at)) {
3037  // Leave some space so we have enough gap room.
3038  revisit_at = revisit_at.PrevStart().FullStart();
3039  }
3040  // If this range became life right at the block boundary that we are
3041  // currently processing, we do not need to split it. Instead move it
3042  // to unhandled right away.
3043  if (position < revisit_at) {
3044  LiveRange* third_part = SplitRangeAt(split, revisit_at);
3045  DCHECK_NE(split, third_part);
3046  Spill(split, spill_mode);
3047  TRACE("Marking %d:%d to recombine\n", toplevel->vreg(),
3048  third_part->relative_id());
3049  third_part->SetRecombine();
3050  AddToUnhandled(third_part);
3051  } else {
3052  AddToUnhandled(split);
3053  }
3054  } else {
3055  Spill(split, spill_mode);
3056  }
3057  it = ActiveToHandled(it);
3058  }
3059  } else {
3060  // This range is contained in {to_be_live}, so we can keep it.
3061  int expected_register = found->second;
3062  to_be_live.erase(found);
3063  if (expected_register == active_range->assigned_register()) {
3064  // Was life and in correct register, simply pass through.
3065  TRACE("Keeping %d:%d in %s\n", toplevel->vreg(),
3066  active_range->relative_id(),
3067  RegisterName(active_range->assigned_register()));
3068  ++it;
3069  } else {
3070  // Was life but wrong register. Split and schedule for
3071  // allocation.
3072  TRACE("Scheduling %d:%d\n", toplevel->vreg(),
3073  active_range->relative_id());
3074  LiveRange* split = SplitRangeAt(active_range, position);
3075  split->set_controlflow_hint(expected_register);
3076  AddToUnhandled(split);
3077  it = ActiveToHandled(it);
3078  }
3079  }
3080  }
3081 }
3082 
3083 LiveRange* LinearScanAllocator::AssignRegisterOnReload(LiveRange* range,
3084  int reg) {
3085  // We know the register is currently free but it might be in
3086  // use by a currently inactive range. So we might not be able
3087  // to reload for the full distance. In such case, split here.
3088  // TODO(herhut):
3089  // It might be better if we could use the normal unhandled queue and
3090  // give reloading registers pecedence. That way we would compute the
3091  // intersection for the entire future.
3092  LifetimePosition new_end = range->End();
3093  for (int cur_reg = 0; cur_reg < num_registers(); ++cur_reg) {
3094  if ((kFPAliasing != AliasingKind::kCombine || !check_fp_aliasing()) &&
3095  cur_reg != reg) {
3096  continue;
3097  }
3098  SlowDCheckInactiveLiveRangesIsSorted(cur_reg);
3099  for (LiveRange* cur_inactive : inactive_live_ranges(cur_reg)) {
3100  if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kCombine && check_fp_aliasing() &&
3101  !data()->config()->AreAliases(cur_inactive->representation(), cur_reg,
3102  range->representation(), reg)) {
3103  continue;
3104  }
3105  if (new_end <= cur_inactive->NextStart()) {
3106  // Inactive ranges are sorted by their next start, so the remaining
3107  // ranges cannot contribute to new_end.
3108  break;
3109  }
3110  auto next_intersection = cur_inactive->FirstIntersection(range);
3111  if (!next_intersection.IsValid()) continue;
3112  new_end = std::min(new_end, next_intersection);
3113  }
3114  }
3115  if (new_end != range->End()) {
3116  TRACE("Found new end for %d:%d at %d\n", range->TopLevel()->vreg(),
3117  range->relative_id(), new_end.value());
3118  LiveRange* tail = SplitRangeAt(range, new_end);
3119  AddToUnhandled(tail);
3120  }
3121  SetLiveRangeAssignedRegister(range, reg);
3122  return range;
3123 }
3124 
3125 void LinearScanAllocator::ReloadLiveRanges(
3126  RangeRegisterSmallMap const& to_be_live, LifetimePosition position) {
3127  // Assumption: All ranges in {to_be_live} are currently spilled and there are
3128  // no conflicting registers in the active ranges.
3129  // The former is ensured by SpillNotLiveRanges, the latter is by construction
3130  // of the to_be_live set.
3131  for (auto [range, reg] : to_be_live) {
3132  LiveRange* to_resurrect = range->GetChildCovers(position);
3133  if (to_resurrect == nullptr) {
3134  // While the range was life until the end of the predecessor block, it is
3135  // not live in this block. Either there is a lifetime gap or the range
3136  // died.
3137  TRACE("No candidate for %d at %d\n", range->vreg(), position.value());
3138  } else {
3139  // We might be resurrecting a range that we spilled until its next use
3140  // before. In such cases, we have to unsplit it before processing as
3141  // otherwise we might get register changes from one range to the other
3142  // in the middle of blocks.
3143  // If there is a gap between this range and the next, we can just keep
3144  // it as a register change won't hurt.
3145  MaybeUndoPreviousSplit(to_resurrect, allocation_zone());
3146  if (to_resurrect->Start() == position) {
3147  // This range already starts at this block. It might have been spilled,
3148  // so we have to unspill it. Otherwise, it is already in the unhandled
3149  // queue waiting for processing.
3150  DCHECK(!to_resurrect->HasRegisterAssigned());
3151  TRACE("Reload %d:%d starting at %d itself\n", range->vreg(),
3152  to_resurrect->relative_id(), position.value());
3153  if (to_resurrect->spilled()) {
3154  to_resurrect->Unspill();
3155  to_resurrect->set_controlflow_hint(reg);
3156  AddToUnhandled(to_resurrect);
3157  } else {
3158  // Assign the preassigned register if we know. Otherwise, nothing to
3159  // do as already in unhandeled.
3160  if (reg != kUnassignedRegister) {
3161  auto erased_cnt = unhandled_live_ranges().erase(to_resurrect);
3162  DCHECK_EQ(erased_cnt, 1);
3163  USE(erased_cnt);
3164  // We know that there is no conflict with active ranges, so just
3165  // assign the register to the range.
3166  to_resurrect = AssignRegisterOnReload(to_resurrect, reg);
3167  AddToActive(to_resurrect);
3168  }
3169  }
3170  } else {
3171  // This range was spilled before. We have to split it and schedule the
3172  // second part for allocation (or assign the register if we know).
3173  DCHECK(to_resurrect->spilled());
3174  LiveRange* split = SplitRangeAt(to_resurrect, position);
3175  TRACE("Reload %d:%d starting at %d as %d\n", range->vreg(),
3176  to_resurrect->relative_id(), split->Start().value(),
3177  split->relative_id());
3178  DCHECK_NE(split, to_resurrect);
3179  if (reg != kUnassignedRegister) {
3180  // We know that there is no conflict with active ranges, so just
3181  // assign the register to the range.
3182  split = AssignRegisterOnReload(split, reg);
3183  AddToActive(split);
3184  } else {
3185  // Let normal register assignment find a suitable register.
3186  split->set_controlflow_hint(reg);
3187  AddToUnhandled(split);
3188  }
3189  }
3190  }
3191  }
3192 }
3193 
3194 RpoNumber LinearScanAllocator::ChooseOneOfTwoPredecessorStates(
3195  InstructionBlock* current_block, LifetimePosition boundary) {
3196  // Pick the state that would generate the least spill/reloads.
3197  // Compute vectors of ranges with use counts for both sides.
3198  // We count uses only for live ranges that are unique to either the left or
3199  // the right predecessor since many live ranges are shared between both.
3200  // Shared ranges don't influence the decision anyway and this is faster.
3201  auto& left = data()->GetSpillState(current_block->predecessors()[0]);
3202  auto& right = data()->GetSpillState(current_block->predecessors()[1]);
3203 
3204  // Build a set of the `TopLevelLiveRange`s in the left predecessor.
3205  // Usually this set is very small, e.g., for JetStream2 at most 3 ranges in
3206  // ~72% of the cases and at most 8 ranges in ~93% of the cases. In those cases
3207  // `SmallMap` is backed by inline storage and uses fast linear search.
