3208  // In some pathological cases the set grows large (e.g. the Wasm binary of
3209  // v8:9529) and then `SmallMap` gives us O(log n) worst case lookup when
3210  // intersecting with the right predecessor below. The set is encoded as a
3211  // `SmallMap` to `Dummy` values, since we don't have an equivalent `SmallSet`.
3212  struct Dummy {};
3213  SmallZoneMap<TopLevelLiveRange*, Dummy, 16> left_set(allocation_zone());
3214  for (LiveRange* range : left) {
3215  TopLevelLiveRange* parent = range->TopLevel();
3216  auto [_, inserted] = left_set.emplace(parent, Dummy{});
3217  // The `LiveRange`s in `left` come from the spill state, which is just the
3218  // list of active `LiveRange`s at the end of the block (see
3219  // `RememberSpillState`). Since at most one `LiveRange` out of a
3220  // `TopLevelLiveRange` can be active at the same time, there should never be
3221  // the same `TopLevelLiveRange` twice in `left_set`, hence this check.
3222  DCHECK(inserted);
3223  USE(inserted);
3224  }
3225 
3226  // Now build a list of ranges unique to either the left or right predecessor.
3227  struct RangeUseCount {
3228  // The set above contains `TopLevelLiveRange`s, but ultimately we want to
3229  // count uses of the child `LiveRange` covering `boundary`.
3230  // The lookup in `GetChildCovers` is O(log n), so do it only once when
3231  // inserting into this list.
3232  LiveRange* range;
3233  // +1 if used in the left predecessor, -1 if used in the right predecessor.
3234  int use_count_delta;
3235  };
3236  SmallZoneVector<RangeUseCount, 16> unique_range_use_counts(allocation_zone());
3237  for (LiveRange* range : right) {
3238  TopLevelLiveRange* parent = range->TopLevel();
3239  auto left_it = left_set.find(parent);
3240  bool range_is_shared_left_and_right = left_it != left_set.end();
3241  if (range_is_shared_left_and_right) {
3242  left_set.erase(left_it);
3243  } else {
3244  // This range is unique to the right predecessor, so insert into the list.
3245  LiveRange* child = parent->GetChildCovers(boundary);
3246  if (child != nullptr) {
3247  unique_range_use_counts.push_back({child, -1});
3248  }
3249  }
3250  }
3251  // So far `unique_range_use_counts` contains only the ranges unique in the
3252  // right predecessor. Now also add the ranges from the left predecessor.
3253  for (auto [parent, _] : left_set) {
3254  LiveRange* child = parent->GetChildCovers(boundary);
3255  if (child != nullptr) {
3256  unique_range_use_counts.push_back({child, +1});
3257  }
3258  }
3259 
3260  // Finally, count the uses for each range.
3261  int use_count_difference = 0;
3262  for (auto [range, use_count] : unique_range_use_counts) {
3263  if (range->NextUsePositionRegisterIsBeneficial(boundary) != nullptr) {
3264  use_count_difference += use_count;
3265  }
3266  }
3267  if (use_count_difference == 0) {
3268  // There is a tie in beneficial register uses. Now, look at any use at all.
3269  // We do not account for all uses, like flowing into a phi.
3270  // So we just look at ranges still being live.
3271  TRACE("Looking at only uses\n");
3272  for (auto [range, use_count] : unique_range_use_counts) {
3273  if (range->NextUsePosition(boundary) != range->positions().end()) {
3274  use_count_difference += use_count;
3275  }
3276  }
3277  }
3278  TRACE("Left predecessor has %d more uses than right\n", use_count_difference);
3279  return use_count_difference > 0 ? current_block->predecessors()[0]
3280  : current_block->predecessors()[1];
3281 }
3282 
3283 bool LinearScanAllocator::CheckConflict(
3284  MachineRepresentation rep, int reg,
3285  const RangeRegisterSmallMap& to_be_live) {
3286  for (auto [range, expected_reg] : to_be_live) {
3287  if (data()->config()->AreAliases(range->representation(), expected_reg, rep,
3288  reg)) {
3289  return true;
3290  }
3291  }
3292  return false;
3293 }
3294 
3295 void LinearScanAllocator::ComputeStateFromManyPredecessors(
3296  InstructionBlock* current_block, RangeRegisterSmallMap& to_be_live) {
3297  struct Vote {
3298  size_t count;
3299  int used_registers[RegisterConfiguration::kMaxRegisters];
3300  explicit Vote(int reg) : count(1), used_registers{0} {
3301  used_registers[reg] = 1;
3302  }
3303  };
3304  struct TopLevelLiveRangeComparator {
3305  bool operator()(const TopLevelLiveRange* lhs,
3306  const TopLevelLiveRange* rhs) const {
3307  return lhs->vreg() < rhs->vreg();
3308  }
3309  };
3310  // Typically this map is very small, e.g., on JetStream2 it has at most 3
3311  // elements ~80% of the time and at most 8 elements ~94% of the time.
3312  // Thus use a `SmallZoneMap` to avoid allocations and because linear search
3313  // in an array is faster than map lookup for such small sizes.
3314  // We don't want too many inline elements though since `Vote` is pretty large.
3315  using RangeVoteMap =
3316  SmallZoneMap<TopLevelLiveRange*, Vote, 16, TopLevelLiveRangeComparator>;
3317  static_assert(sizeof(RangeVoteMap) < 4096, "too large stack allocation");
3318  RangeVoteMap counts(data()->allocation_zone());
3319 
3320  int deferred_blocks = 0;
3321  for (RpoNumber pred : current_block->predecessors()) {
3322  if (!ConsiderBlockForControlFlow(current_block, pred)) {
3323  // Back edges of a loop count as deferred here too.
3324  deferred_blocks++;
3325  continue;
3326  }
3327  const auto& pred_state = data()->GetSpillState(pred);
3328  for (LiveRange* range : pred_state) {
3329  // We might have spilled the register backwards, so the range we
3330  // stored might have lost its register. Ignore those.
3331  if (!range->HasRegisterAssigned()) continue;
3332  TopLevelLiveRange* toplevel = range->TopLevel();
3333  auto [it, inserted] =
3334  counts.try_emplace(toplevel, range->assigned_register());
3335  if (!inserted) {
3336  it->second.count++;
3337  it->second.used_registers[range->assigned_register()]++;
3338  }
3339  }
3340  }
3341 
3342  // Choose the live ranges from the majority.
3343  const size_t majority =
3344  (current_block->PredecessorCount() + 2 - deferred_blocks) / 2;
3345  bool taken_registers[RegisterConfiguration::kMaxRegisters] = {false};
3346  DCHECK(to_be_live.empty());
3347  auto assign_to_live = [this, majority, &counts](
3348  std::function<bool(TopLevelLiveRange*)> filter,
3349  RangeRegisterSmallMap& to_be_live,
3350  bool* taken_registers) {
3351  bool check_aliasing =
3352  kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kCombine && check_fp_aliasing();
3353  for (const auto& val : counts) {
3354  if (!filter(val.first)) continue;
3355  if (val.second.count >= majority) {
3356  int register_max = 0;
3357  int reg = kUnassignedRegister;
3358  bool conflict = false;
3359  int num_regs = num_registers();
3360  int num_codes = num_allocatable_registers();
3361  const int* codes = allocatable_register_codes();
3362  MachineRepresentation rep = val.first->representation();
3363  if (check_aliasing && (rep == MachineRepresentation::kFloat32 ||
3364  rep == MachineRepresentation::kSimd128 ||
3365  rep == MachineRepresentation::kSimd256))
3366  GetFPRegisterSet(rep, &num_regs, &num_codes, &codes);
3367  for (int idx = 0; idx < num_regs; idx++) {
3368  int uses = val.second.used_registers[idx];
3369  if (uses == 0) continue;
3370  if (uses > register_max || (conflict && uses == register_max)) {
3371  reg = idx;
3372  register_max = uses;
3373  conflict = check_aliasing ? CheckConflict(rep, reg, to_be_live)
3374  : taken_registers[reg];
3375  }
3376  }
3377  if (conflict) {
3378  reg = kUnassignedRegister;
3379  } else if (!check_aliasing) {
3380  taken_registers[reg] = true;
3381  }
3382  TRACE("Reset %d as live due vote %zu in %s\n", val.first->vreg(),
3383  val.second.count, RegisterName(reg));
3384  auto [_, inserted] = to_be_live.emplace(val.first, reg);
3385  DCHECK(inserted);
3386  USE(inserted);
3387  }
3388  }
3389  };
3390  // First round, process fixed registers, as these have precedence.
3391  // There is only one fixed range per register, so we cannot have
3392  // conflicts.
3393  assign_to_live([](TopLevelLiveRange* r) { return r->IsFixed(); }, to_be_live,
3394  taken_registers);
3395  // Second round, process the rest.
3396  assign_to_live([](TopLevelLiveRange* r) { return !r->IsFixed(); }, to_be_live,
3397  taken_registers);
3398 }
3399 
3400 bool LinearScanAllocator::ConsiderBlockForControlFlow(
3401  InstructionBlock* current_block, RpoNumber predecessor) {
3402  // We ignore predecessors on back edges when looking for control flow effects,
3403  // as those lie in the future of allocation and we have no data yet. Also,
3404  // deferred bocks are ignored on deferred to non-deferred boundaries, as we do
3405  // not want them to influence allocation of non deferred code.
3406  return (predecessor < current_block->rpo_number()) &&
3407  (current_block->IsDeferred() ||
3408  !code()->InstructionBlockAt(predecessor)->IsDeferred());
3409 }
3410 
3411 void LinearScanAllocator::UpdateDeferredFixedRanges(SpillMode spill_mode,
3412  InstructionBlock* block) {
3413  if (spill_mode == SpillMode::kSpillDeferred) {
3414  LifetimePosition max = LifetimePosition::InstructionFromInstructionIndex(
3415  LastDeferredInstructionIndex(block));
3416  // Adds range back to inactive, resolving resulting conflicts.
3417  auto add_to_inactive = [this, max](LiveRange* range) {
3418  AddToInactive(range);
3419  // Splits other if it conflicts with range. Other is placed in unhandled
3420  // for later reallocation.
3421  auto split_conflicting = [this, max](LiveRange* range, LiveRange* other,
3422  std::function<void(LiveRange*)>
3423  update_caches) {
3424  if (other->TopLevel()->IsFixed()) return;
3425  int reg = range->assigned_register();
3426  if (kFPAliasing != AliasingKind::kCombine || !check_fp_aliasing()) {
3427  if (other->assigned_register() != reg) {
3428  return;
3429  }
3430  } else {
3431  if (!data()->config()->AreAliases(range->representation(), reg,
3432  other->representation(),
3433  other->assigned_register())) {
3434  return;
3435  }
3436  }
3437  // The inactive range might conflict, so check whether we need to
3438  // split and spill. We can look for the first intersection, as there
3439  // cannot be any intersections in the past, as those would have been a
3440  // conflict then.
3441  LifetimePosition next_start = range->FirstIntersection(other);
3442  if (!next_start.IsValid() || (next_start > max)) {
3443  // There is no conflict or the conflict is outside of the current
3444  // stretch of deferred code. In either case we can ignore the
3445  // inactive range.
3446  return;
3447  }
3448  // They overlap. So we need to split active and reschedule it
3449  // for allocation.
3450  TRACE("Resolving conflict of %d with deferred fixed for register %s\n",
3451  other->TopLevel()->vreg(),
3452  RegisterName(other->assigned_register()));
3453  LiveRange* split_off =
3454  other->SplitAt(next_start, data()->allocation_zone());
3455  // Try to get the same register after the deferred block.
3456  split_off->set_controlflow_hint(other->assigned_register());
3457  DCHECK_NE(split_off, other);
3458  AddToUnhandled(split_off);
3459  update_caches(other);
3460  };
3461  // Now check for conflicts in active and inactive ranges. We might have
3462  // conflicts in inactive, as we do not do this check on every block
3463  // boundary but only on deferred/non-deferred changes but inactive
3464  // live ranges might become live on any block boundary.
3465  for (auto active : active_live_ranges()) {
3466  split_conflicting(range, active, [this](LiveRange* updated) {
3467  next_active_ranges_change_ =
3468  std::min(updated->End(), next_active_ranges_change_);
3469  });
3470  }
3471  for (int reg = 0; reg < num_registers(); ++reg) {
3472  if ((kFPAliasing != AliasingKind::kCombine || !check_fp_aliasing()) &&
3473  reg != range->assigned_register()) {
3474  continue;
3475  }
3476  SlowDCheckInactiveLiveRangesIsSorted(reg);
3477  for (auto inactive : inactive_live_ranges(reg)) {
3478  if (inactive->NextStart() > max) break;
3479  split_conflicting(range, inactive, [this](LiveRange* updated) {
3480  next_inactive_ranges_change_ =
3481  std::min(updated->End(), next_inactive_ranges_change_);
3482  });
3483  }
3484  }
3485  };
3486  if (mode() == RegisterKind::kGeneral) {
3487  for (TopLevelLiveRange* current : data()->fixed_live_ranges()) {
3488  if (current != nullptr) {
3489  if (current->IsDeferredFixed()) {
3490  add_to_inactive(current);
3491  }
3492  }
3493  }
3494  } else if (mode() == RegisterKind::kDouble) {
3495  for (TopLevelLiveRange* current : data()->fixed_double_live_ranges()) {
3496  if (current != nullptr) {
3497  if (current->IsDeferredFixed()) {
3498  add_to_inactive(current);
3499  }
3500  }
3501  }
3502  if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kCombine && check_fp_aliasing()) {
3503  for (TopLevelLiveRange* current : data()->fixed_float_live_ranges()) {
3504  if (current != nullptr) {
3505  if (current->IsDeferredFixed()) {
3506  add_to_inactive(current);
3507  }
3508  }
3509  }
3510  for (TopLevelLiveRange* current : data()->fixed_simd128_live_ranges()) {
3511  if (current != nullptr) {
3512  if (current->IsDeferredFixed()) {
3513  add_to_inactive(current);
3514  }
3515  }
3516  }
3517  }
3518  } else {
3519  DCHECK_EQ(mode(), RegisterKind::kSimd128);
3520  for (TopLevelLiveRange* current : data()->fixed_simd128_live_ranges()) {
3521  if (current != nullptr) {
3522  if (current->IsDeferredFixed()) {
3523  add_to_inactive(current);
3524  }
3525  }
3526  }
3527  }
3528  } else {
3529  // Remove all ranges.
3530  for (int reg = 0; reg < num_registers(); ++reg) {
3531  for (auto it = inactive_live_ranges(reg).begin();
3532  it != inactive_live_ranges(reg).end();) {
3533  if ((*it)->TopLevel()->IsDeferredFixed()) {
3534  it = inactive_live_ranges(reg).erase(it);
3535  } else {
3536  ++it;
3537  }
3538  }
3539  }
3540  }
3541 }
3542 
3543 bool LinearScanAllocator::BlockIsDeferredOrImmediatePredecessorIsNotDeferred(
3544  const InstructionBlock* block) {
3545  if (block->IsDeferred()) return true;
3546  if (block->PredecessorCount() == 0) return true;
3547  bool pred_is_deferred = false;
3548  for (auto pred : block->predecessors()) {
3549  if (pred.IsNext(block->rpo_number())) {
3550  pred_is_deferred = code()->InstructionBlockAt(pred)->IsDeferred();
3551  break;
3552  }
3553  }
3554  return !pred_is_deferred;
3555 }
3556 
3557 bool LinearScanAllocator::HasNonDeferredPredecessor(InstructionBlock* block) {
3558  for (auto pred : block->predecessors()) {
3559  InstructionBlock* pred_block = code()->InstructionBlockAt(pred);
3560  if (!pred_block->IsDeferred()) return true;
3561  }
3562  return false;
3563 }
3564 
3565 void LinearScanAllocator::AllocateRegisters() {
3566  DCHECK(unhandled_live_ranges().empty());
3567  DCHECK(active_live_ranges().empty());
3568  for (int reg = 0; reg < num_registers(); ++reg) {
3569  DCHECK(inactive_live_ranges(reg).empty());
3570  }
3571 
3572  SplitAndSpillRangesDefinedByMemoryOperand();
3573  data()->ResetSpillState();
3574 
3575  if (v8_flags.trace_turbo_alloc) {
3576  PrintRangeOverview();
3577  }
3578 
3579  const size_t live_ranges_size = data()->live_ranges().size();
3580  for (TopLevelLiveRange* range : data()->live_ranges()) {
3581  CHECK_EQ(live_ranges_size,
3582  data()->live_ranges().size()); // TODO(neis): crbug.com/831822
3583  if (!CanProcessRange(range)) continue;
3584  for (LiveRange* to_add = range; to_add != nullptr;
3585  to_add = to_add->next()) {
3586  if (!to_add->spilled()) {
3587  AddToUnhandled(to_add);
3588  }
3589  }
3590  }
3591 
3592  if (mode() == RegisterKind::kGeneral) {
3593  for (TopLevelLiveRange* current : data()->fixed_live_ranges()) {
3594  if (current != nullptr) {
3595  if (current->IsDeferredFixed()) continue;
3596  AddToInactive(current);
3597  }
3598  }
3599  } else if (mode() == RegisterKind::kDouble) {
3600  for (TopLevelLiveRange* current : data()->fixed_double_live_ranges()) {
3601  if (current != nullptr) {
3602  if (current->IsDeferredFixed()) continue;
3603  AddToInactive(current);
3604  }
3605  }
3606  if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kCombine && check_fp_aliasing()) {
3607  for (TopLevelLiveRange* current : data()->fixed_float_live_ranges()) {
3608  if (current != nullptr) {
3609  if (current->IsDeferredFixed()) continue;
3610  AddToInactive(current);
3611  }
3612  }
3613  for (TopLevelLiveRange* current : data()->fixed_simd128_live_ranges()) {
3614  if (current != nullptr) {
3615  if (current->IsDeferredFixed()) continue;
3616  AddToInactive(current);
3617  }
3618  }
3619  }
3620  } else {
3621  DCHECK(mode() == RegisterKind::kSimd128);
3622  for (TopLevelLiveRange* current : data()->fixed_simd128_live_ranges()) {
3623  if (current != nullptr) {
3624  if (current->IsDeferredFixed()) continue;
3625  AddToInactive(current);
3626  }
3627  }
3628  }
3629 
3630  RpoNumber last_block = RpoNumber::FromInt(0);
3631  RpoNumber max_blocks =
3632  RpoNumber::FromInt(code()->InstructionBlockCount() - 1);
3633  LifetimePosition next_block_boundary =
3634  LifetimePosition::InstructionFromInstructionIndex(
3635  data()
3636  ->code()
3637  ->InstructionBlockAt(last_block)
3638  ->last_instruction_index())
3639  .NextFullStart();
3640  SpillMode spill_mode = SpillMode::kSpillAtDefinition;
3641 
3642  // Process all ranges. We also need to ensure that we have seen all block
3643  // boundaries. Linear scan might have assigned and spilled ranges before
3644  // reaching the last block and hence we would ignore control flow effects for
3645  // those. Not only does this produce a potentially bad assignment, it also
3646  // breaks with the invariant that we undo spills that happen in deferred code
3647  // when crossing a deferred/non-deferred boundary.
3648  while (!unhandled_live_ranges().empty() || last_block < max_blocks) {
3649  data()->tick_counter()->TickAndMaybeEnterSafepoint();
3650  LiveRange* current = unhandled_live_ranges().empty()
3651  ? nullptr
3652  : *unhandled_live_ranges().begin();
3653  LifetimePosition position =
3654  current ? current->Start() : next_block_boundary;
3655 #ifdef DEBUG
3656  allocation_finger_ = position;
3657 #endif
3658  // Check whether we just moved across a block boundary. This will trigger
3659  // for the first range that is past the current boundary.
3660  if (position >= next_block_boundary) {
3661  TRACE("Processing boundary at %d leaving %d\n",
3662  next_block_boundary.value(), last_block.ToInt());
3663 
3664  // Forward state to before block boundary
3665  LifetimePosition end_of_block = next_block_boundary.PrevStart().End();
3666  ForwardStateTo(end_of_block);
3667 
3668  // Remember this state.
3669  InstructionBlock* current_block = data()->code()->GetInstructionBlock(
3670  next_block_boundary.ToInstructionIndex());
3671 
3672  // Store current spill state (as the state at end of block). For
3673  // simplicity, we store the active ranges, e.g., the live ranges that
3674  // are not spilled.
3675  data()->RememberSpillState(last_block, active_live_ranges());
3676 
3677  // Only reset the state if this was not a direct fallthrough. Otherwise
3678  // control flow resolution will get confused (it does not expect changes
3679  // across fallthrough edges.).
3680  bool fallthrough =
3681  (current_block->PredecessorCount() == 1) &&
3682  current_block->predecessors()[0].IsNext(current_block->rpo_number());
3683 
3684  // When crossing a deferred/non-deferred boundary, we have to load or
3685  // remove the deferred fixed ranges from inactive.
3686  if ((spill_mode == SpillMode::kSpillDeferred) !=
3687  current_block->IsDeferred()) {
3688  // Update spill mode.
3689  spill_mode = current_block->IsDeferred()
3690  ? SpillMode::kSpillDeferred
3691  : SpillMode::kSpillAtDefinition;
3692 
3693  ForwardStateTo(next_block_boundary);
3694 
3695 #ifdef DEBUG
3696  // Allow allocation at current position.
3697  allocation_finger_ = next_block_boundary;
3698 #endif
3699  UpdateDeferredFixedRanges(spill_mode, current_block);
3700  }
3701 
3702  // Allocation relies on the fact that each non-deferred block has at
3703  // least one non-deferred predecessor. Check this invariant here.
3704  DCHECK_IMPLIES(!current_block->IsDeferred(),
3705  HasNonDeferredPredecessor(current_block));
3706 
3707  if (!fallthrough) {
3708 #ifdef DEBUG
3709  // Allow allocation at current position.
3710  allocation_finger_ = next_block_boundary;
3711 #endif
3712 
3713  // We are currently at next_block_boundary - 1. Move the state to the
3714  // actual block boundary position. In particular, we have to
3715  // reactivate inactive ranges so that they get rescheduled for
3716  // allocation if they were not live at the predecessors.
3717  ForwardStateTo(next_block_boundary);
3718 
3719  RangeRegisterSmallMap to_be_live(allocation_zone());
3720 
3721  // If we end up deciding to use the state of the immediate
3722  // predecessor, it is better not to perform a change. It would lead to
3723  // the same outcome anyway.
3724  // This may never happen on boundaries between deferred and
3725  // non-deferred code, as we rely on explicit respill to ensure we
3726  // spill at definition.
3727  bool no_change_required = false;
3728 
3729  auto pick_state_from = [this, current_block](
3730  RpoNumber pred,
3731  RangeRegisterSmallMap& to_be_live) -> bool {
3732  TRACE("Using information from B%d\n", pred.ToInt());
3733  // If this is a fall-through that is not across a deferred
3734  // boundary, there is nothing to do.
3735  bool is_noop = pred.IsNext(current_block->rpo_number());
3736  if (!is_noop) {
3737  auto& spill_state = data()->GetSpillState(pred);
3738  TRACE("Not a fallthrough. Adding %zu elements...\n",
3739  spill_state.size());
3740  LifetimePosition pred_end =
3741  LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(
3742  this->code()->InstructionBlockAt(pred)->code_end());
3743  DCHECK(to_be_live.empty());
3744  for (const auto range : spill_state) {
3745  // Filter out ranges that were split or had their register
3746  // stolen by backwards working spill heuristics. These have
3747  // been spilled after the fact, so ignore them.
3748  if (range->End() < pred_end || !range->HasRegisterAssigned())
3749  continue;
3750  auto [_, inserted] = to_be_live.emplace(
3751  range->TopLevel(), range->assigned_register());
3752  DCHECK(inserted);
3753  USE(inserted);
3754  }
3755  }
3756  return is_noop;
3757  };
3758 
3759  // Multiple cases here:
3760  // 1) We have a single predecessor => this is a control flow split, so
3761  // just restore the predecessor state.
3762  // 2) We have two predecessors => this is a conditional, so break ties
3763  // based on what to do based on forward uses, trying to benefit
3764  // the same branch if in doubt (make one path fast).
3765  // 3) We have many predecessors => this is a switch. Compute union
3766  // based on majority, break ties by looking forward.
3767  if (current_block->PredecessorCount() == 1) {
3768  TRACE("Single predecessor for B%d\n",
3769  current_block->rpo_number().ToInt());
3770  no_change_required =
3771  pick_state_from(current_block->predecessors()[0], to_be_live);
3772  } else if (current_block->PredecessorCount() == 2) {
3773  TRACE("Two predecessors for B%d\n",
3774  current_block->rpo_number().ToInt());
3775  // If one of the branches does not contribute any information,
3776  // e.g. because it is deferred or a back edge, we can short cut
3777  // here right away.
3778  RpoNumber chosen_predecessor = RpoNumber::Invalid();
3779  if (!ConsiderBlockForControlFlow(current_block,
3780  current_block->predecessors()[0])) {
3781  chosen_predecessor = current_block->predecessors()[1];
3782  } else if (!ConsiderBlockForControlFlow(
3783  current_block, current_block->predecessors()[1])) {
3784  chosen_predecessor = current_block->predecessors()[0];
3785  } else {
3786  chosen_predecessor = ChooseOneOfTwoPredecessorStates(
3787  current_block, next_block_boundary);
3788  }
3789  no_change_required = pick_state_from(chosen_predecessor, to_be_live);
3790 
3791  } else {
3792  // Merge at the end of, e.g., a switch.
3793  ComputeStateFromManyPredecessors(current_block, to_be_live);
3794  }
3795 
3796  if (!no_change_required) {
3797  SpillNotLiveRanges(to_be_live, next_block_boundary, spill_mode);
3798  ReloadLiveRanges(to_be_live, next_block_boundary);
3799  }
3800  }
3801  // Update block information
3802  last_block = current_block->rpo_number();
3803  next_block_boundary = LifetimePosition::InstructionFromInstructionIndex(
3804  current_block->last_instruction_index())
3805  .NextFullStart();
3806 
3807  // We might have created new unhandled live ranges, so cycle around the
3808  // loop to make sure we pick the top most range in unhandled for
3809  // processing.
3810  continue;
3811  }
3812 
3813  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(current);
3814 
3815  TRACE("Processing interval %d:%d start=%d\n", current->TopLevel()->vreg(),
3816  current->relative_id(), position.value());
3817 
3818  // Now we can erase current, as we are sure to process it.
3819  unhandled_live_ranges().erase(unhandled_live_ranges().begin());
3820 
3821  if (current->IsTopLevel() && TryReuseSpillForPhi(current->TopLevel()))
3822  continue;
3823 
3824  ForwardStateTo(position);
3825 
3826  DCHECK(!current->HasRegisterAssigned() && !current->spilled());
3827 
3828  ProcessCurrentRange(current, spill_mode);
3829  }
3830 
3831  if (v8_flags.trace_turbo_alloc) {
3832  PrintRangeOverview();
3833  }
3834 }
3835 
3836 void LinearScanAllocator::SetLiveRangeAssignedRegister(LiveRange* range,
3837  int reg) {
3838  data()->MarkAllocated(range->representation(), reg);
3839  range->set_assigned_register(reg);
3840  range->SetUseHints(reg);
3841  range->UpdateBundleRegister(reg);
3842  if (range->IsTopLevel() && range->TopLevel()->is_phi()) {
3843  data()->GetPhiMapValueFor(range->TopLevel())->set_assigned_register(reg);
3844  }
3845 }
3846 
3847 void LinearScanAllocator::AddToActive(LiveRange* range) {
3848  TRACE("Add live range %d:%d in %s to active\n", range->TopLevel()->vreg(),
3849  range->relative_id(), RegisterName(range->assigned_register()));
3850  active_live_ranges().push_back(range);
3851  next_active_ranges_change_ =
3852  std::min(next_active_ranges_change_, range->NextEndAfter(range->Start()));
3853 }
3854 
3855 void LinearScanAllocator::AddToInactive(LiveRange* range) {
3856  TRACE("Add live range %d:%d to inactive\n", range->TopLevel()->vreg(),
3857  range->relative_id());
3858  next_inactive_ranges_change_ = std::min(
3859  next_inactive_ranges_change_, range->NextStartAfter(range->Start()));
3860  DCHECK(range->HasRegisterAssigned());
3861  // Keep `inactive_live_ranges` sorted.
3862  inactive_live_ranges(range->assigned_register())
3863  .insert(std::upper_bound(
3864  inactive_live_ranges(range->assigned_register()).begin(),
3865  inactive_live_ranges(range->assigned_register()).end(), range,
3866  InactiveLiveRangeOrdering()),
3867  1, range);
3868 }
3869 
3870 void LinearScanAllocator::AddToUnhandled(LiveRange* range) {
3871  if (range == nullptr || range->IsEmpty()) return;
3872  DCHECK(!range->HasRegisterAssigned() && !range->spilled());
3873  DCHECK(allocation_finger_ <= range->Start());
3874 
3875  TRACE("Add live range %d:%d to unhandled\n", range->TopLevel()->vreg(),
3876  range->relative_id());
3877  unhandled_live_ranges().insert(range);
3878 }
3879 
3880 ZoneVector<LiveRange*>::iterator LinearScanAllocator::ActiveToHandled(
3881  const ZoneVector<LiveRange*>::iterator it) {
3882  TRACE("Moving live range %d:%d from active to handled\n",
3883  (*it)->TopLevel()->vreg(), (*it)->relative_id());
3884  return active_live_ranges().erase(it);
3885 }
3886 
3887 ZoneVector<LiveRange*>::iterator LinearScanAllocator::ActiveToInactive(
3888  const ZoneVector<LiveRange*>::iterator it, LifetimePosition position) {
3889  LiveRange* range = *it;
3890  TRACE("Moving live range %d:%d from active to inactive\n",
3891  (range)->TopLevel()->vreg(), range->relative_id());
3892  LifetimePosition next_active = range->NextStartAfter(position);
3893  next_inactive_ranges_change_ =
3894  std::min(next_inactive_ranges_change_, next_active);
3895  DCHECK(range->HasRegisterAssigned());
3896  // Keep `inactive_live_ranges` sorted.
3897  inactive_live_ranges(range->assigned_register())
3898  .insert(std::upper_bound(
3899  inactive_live_ranges(range->assigned_register()).begin(),
3900  inactive_live_ranges(range->assigned_register()).end(), range,
3901  InactiveLiveRangeOrdering()),
3902  1, range);
3903  return active_live_ranges().erase(it);
3904 }
3905 
3906 LinearScanAllocator::InactiveLiveRangeQueue::iterator
3907 LinearScanAllocator::InactiveToHandled(InactiveLiveRangeQueue::iterator it) {
3908  LiveRange* range = *it;
3909  TRACE("Moving live range %d:%d from inactive to handled\n",
3910  range->TopLevel()->vreg(), range->relative_id());
3911  int reg = range->assigned_register();
3912  // This must keep the order of `inactive_live_ranges` intact since one of its
3913  // callers `SplitAndSpillIntersecting` relies on it being sorted.
3914  return inactive_live_ranges(reg).erase(it);
3915 }
3916 
3917 LinearScanAllocator::InactiveLiveRangeQueue::iterator
3918 LinearScanAllocator::InactiveToActive(InactiveLiveRangeQueue::iterator it,
3919  LifetimePosition position) {
3920  LiveRange* range = *it;
3921  active_live_ranges().push_back(range);
3922  TRACE("Moving live range %d:%d from inactive to active\n",
3923  range->TopLevel()->vreg(), range->relative_id());
3924  next_active_ranges_change_ =
3925  std::min(next_active_ranges_change_, range->NextEndAfter(position));
3926  int reg = range->assigned_register();
3927  // Remove the element without copying O(n) subsequent elements.
3928  // The order of `inactive_live_ranges` is established afterwards by sorting in
3929  // `ForwardStateTo`, which is the only caller.
3930  std::swap(*it, inactive_live_ranges(reg).back());
3931  inactive_live_ranges(reg).pop_back();
3932  return it;
3933 }
3934 
3935 void LinearScanAllocator::ForwardStateTo(LifetimePosition position) {
3936  if (position >= next_active_ranges_change_) {
3937  next_active_ranges_change_ = LifetimePosition::MaxPosition();
3938  for (auto it = active_live_ranges().begin();
3939  it != active_live_ranges().end();) {
3940  LiveRange* cur_active = *it;
3941  if (cur_active->End() <= position) {
3942  it = ActiveToHandled(it);
3943  } else if (!cur_active->Covers(position)) {
3944  it = ActiveToInactive(it, position);
3945  } else {
3946  next_active_ranges_change_ = std::min(
3947  next_active_ranges_change_, cur_active->NextEndAfter(position));
3948  ++it;
3949  }
3950  }
3951  }
3952 
3953  if (position >= next_inactive_ranges_change_) {
3954  next_inactive_ranges_change_ = LifetimePosition::MaxPosition();
3955  for (int reg = 0; reg < num_registers(); ++reg) {
3956  for (auto it = inactive_live_ranges(reg).begin();
3957  it != inactive_live_ranges(reg).end();) {
3958  LiveRange* cur_inactive = *it;
3959  if (cur_inactive->End() <= position) {
3960  it = InactiveToHandled(it);
3961  } else if (cur_inactive->Covers(position)) {
3962  it = InactiveToActive(it, position);
3963  } else {
3964  next_inactive_ranges_change_ = std::min(
3965  next_inactive_ranges_change_,
3966  // This modifies `cur_inactive.next_start_` and thus
3967  // invalidates the ordering of `inactive_live_ranges(reg)`.
3968  cur_inactive->NextStartAfter(position));
3969  ++it;
3970  }
3971  }
3972  std::sort(inactive_live_ranges(reg).begin(),
3973  inactive_live_ranges(reg).end(), InactiveLiveRangeOrdering());
3974  }
3975  }
3976 
3977  for (int reg = 0; reg < num_registers(); ++reg) {
3978  SlowDCheckInactiveLiveRangesIsSorted(reg);
3979  }
3980 }
3981 
3982 int LinearScanAllocator::LastDeferredInstructionIndex(InstructionBlock* start) {
3983  DCHECK(start->IsDeferred());
3984  RpoNumber last_block =
3985  RpoNumber::FromInt(code()->InstructionBlockCount() - 1);
3986  while ((start->rpo_number() < last_block)) {
3987  InstructionBlock* next =
3988  code()->InstructionBlockAt(start->rpo_number().Next());
3989  if (!next->IsDeferred()) break;
3990  start = next;
3991  }
3992  return start->last_instruction_index();
3993 }
3994 
3995 void LinearScanAllocator::GetFPRegisterSet(MachineRepresentation rep,
3996  int* num_regs, int* num_codes,
3997  const int** codes) const {
3998  DCHECK_EQ(kFPAliasing, AliasingKind::kCombine);
3999  if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kFloat32) {
4000  *num_regs = data()->config()->num_float_registers();
4001  *num_codes = data()->config()->num_allocatable_float_registers();
4002  *codes = data()->config()->allocatable_float_codes();
4003  } else if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kSimd128) {
4004  *num_regs = data()->config()->num_simd128_registers();
4005  *num_codes = data()->config()->num_allocatable_simd128_registers();
4006  *codes = data()->config()->allocatable_simd128_codes();
4007  } else if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kSimd256) {
4008  *num_regs = data()->config()->num_simd256_registers();
4009  *num_codes = data()->config()->num_allocatable_simd256_registers();
4010  *codes = data()->config()->allocatable_simd256_codes();
4011  } else {
4012  UNREACHABLE();
4013  }
4014 }
4015 
4016 void LinearScanAllocator::GetSIMD128RegisterSet(int* num_regs, int* num_codes,
4017  const int** codes) const {
4018  DCHECK_EQ(kFPAliasing, AliasingKind::kIndependent);
4019 
4020  *num_regs = data()->config()->num_simd128_registers();
4021  *num_codes = data()->config()->num_allocatable_simd128_registers();
4022  *codes = data()->config()->allocatable_simd128_codes();
4023 }
4024 
4025 void LinearScanAllocator::FindFreeRegistersForRange(
4026  LiveRange* range, base::Vector<LifetimePosition> positions) {
4027  int num_regs = num_registers();
4028  int num_codes = num_allocatable_registers();
4029  const int* codes = allocatable_register_codes();
4030  MachineRepresentation rep = range->representation();
4031  if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kCombine &&
4032  (rep == MachineRepresentation::kFloat32 ||
4033  rep == MachineRepresentation::kSimd128)) {
4034  GetFPRegisterSet(rep, &num_regs, &num_codes, &codes);
4035  } else if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kIndependent &&
4036  (rep == MachineRepresentation::kSimd128)) {
4037  GetSIMD128RegisterSet(&num_regs, &num_codes, &codes);
4038  }
4039  DCHECK_GE(positions.length(), num_regs);
4040 
4041  for (int i = 0; i < num_regs; ++i) {
4042  positions[i] = LifetimePosition::MaxPosition();
4043  }
4044 
4045  for (LiveRange* cur_active : active_live_ranges()) {
4046  int cur_reg = cur_active->assigned_register();
4047  if (kFPAliasing != AliasingKind::kCombine || !check_fp_aliasing()) {
4048  positions[cur_reg] = LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(0);
4049  TRACE("Register %s is free until pos %d (1) due to %d\n",
4050  RegisterName(cur_reg),
4051  LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(0).value(),
4052  cur_active->TopLevel()->vreg());
4053  } else {
4054  int alias_base_index = -1;
4055  int aliases = data()->config()->GetAliases(
4056  cur_active->representation(), cur_reg, rep, &alias_base_index);
4057  DCHECK(aliases > 0 || (aliases == 0 && alias_base_index == -1));
4058  while (aliases--) {
4059  int aliased_reg = alias_base_index + aliases;
4060  positions[aliased_reg] = LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(0);
4061  }
4062  }
4063  }
4064 
4065  for (int cur_reg = 0; cur_reg < num_regs; ++cur_reg) {
4066  SlowDCheckInactiveLiveRangesIsSorted(cur_reg);
4067  for (LiveRange* cur_inactive : inactive_live_ranges(cur_reg)) {
4068  DCHECK_GT(cur_inactive->End(), range->Start());
4069  DCHECK_EQ(cur_inactive->assigned_register(), cur_reg);
4070  // No need to carry out intersections, when this register won't be
4071  // interesting to this range anyway.
4072  // TODO(mtrofin): extend to aliased ranges, too.
4073  if ((kFPAliasing != AliasingKind::kCombine || !check_fp_aliasing()) &&
4074  (positions[cur_reg] <= cur_inactive->NextStart() ||
4075  range->End() <= cur_inactive->NextStart())) {
4076  break;
4077  }
4078  LifetimePosition next_intersection =
4079  cur_inactive->FirstIntersection(range);
4080  if (!next_intersection.IsValid()) continue;
4081  if (kFPAliasing != AliasingKind::kCombine || !check_fp_aliasing()) {
4082  positions[cur_reg] = std::min(positions[cur_reg], next_intersection);
4083  TRACE("Register %s is free until pos %d (2)\n", RegisterName(cur_reg),
4084  positions[cur_reg].value());
4085  } else {
4086  int alias_base_index = -1;
4087  int aliases = data()->config()->GetAliases(
4088  cur_inactive->representation(), cur_reg, rep, &alias_base_index);
4089  DCHECK(aliases > 0 || (aliases == 0 && alias_base_index == -1));
4090  while (aliases--) {
4091  int aliased_reg = alias_base_index + aliases;
4092  positions[aliased_reg] =
4093  std::min(positions[aliased_reg], next_intersection);
4094  }
4095  }
4096  }
4097  }
4098 }
4099 
4100 // High-level register allocation summary:
4101 //
4102 // We attempt to first allocate the preferred (hint) register. If that is not
4103 // possible, we find a register that's free, and allocate that. If that's not
4104 // possible, we search for a register to steal from a range that was allocated.
4105 // The goal is to optimize for throughput by avoiding register-to-memory moves,
4106 // which are expensive.
4107 void LinearScanAllocator::ProcessCurrentRange(LiveRange* current,
4108  SpillMode spill_mode) {
4109  base::EmbeddedVector<LifetimePosition, RegisterConfiguration::kMaxRegisters>
4110  free_until_pos;
4111  FindFreeRegistersForRange(current, free_until_pos);
4112  if (!TryAllocatePreferredReg(current, free_until_pos)) {
4113  if (!TryAllocateFreeReg(current, free_until_pos)) {
4114  AllocateBlockedReg(current, spill_mode);
4115  }
4116  }
4117  if (current->HasRegisterAssigned()) {
4118  AddToActive(current);
4119  }
4120 }
4121 
4122 bool LinearScanAllocator::TryAllocatePreferredReg(
4123  LiveRange* current, base::Vector<const LifetimePosition> free_until_pos) {
4124  int hint_register;
4125  if (current->RegisterFromControlFlow(&hint_register) ||
4126  current->RegisterFromFirstHint(&hint_register) ||
4127  current->RegisterFromBundle(&hint_register)) {
4128  TRACE(
4129  "Found reg hint %s (free until [%d) for live range %d:%d (end %d[).\n",
4130  RegisterName(hint_register), free_until_pos[hint_register].value(),
4131  current->TopLevel()->vreg(), current->relative_id(),
4132  current->End().value());
4133 
4134  // The desired register is free until the end of the current live range.
4135  if (free_until_pos[hint_register] >= current->End()) {
4136  TRACE("Assigning preferred reg %s to live range %d:%d\n",
4137  RegisterName(hint_register), current->TopLevel()->vreg(),
4138  current->relative_id());
4139  SetLiveRangeAssignedRegister(current, hint_register);
4140  return true;
4141  }
4142  }
4143  return false;
4144 }
4145 
4146 int LinearScanAllocator::PickRegisterThatIsAvailableLongest(
4147  LiveRange* current, int hint_reg,
4148  base::Vector<const LifetimePosition> free_until_pos) {
4149  int num_regs = 0; // used only for the call to GetFPRegisterSet.
4150  int num_codes = num_allocatable_registers();
4151  const int* codes = allocatable_register_codes();
4152  MachineRepresentation rep = current->representation();
4153  if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kCombine &&
4154  (rep == MachineRepresentation::kFloat32 ||
4155  rep == MachineRepresentation::kSimd128)) {
4156  GetFPRegisterSet(rep, &num_regs, &num_codes, &codes);
4157  } else if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kIndependent &&
4158  (rep == MachineRepresentation::kSimd128)) {
4159  GetSIMD128RegisterSet(&num_regs, &num_codes, &codes);
4160  }
4161 
4162  DCHECK_GE(free_until_pos.length(), num_codes);
4163 
4164  // Find the register which stays free for the longest time. Check for
4165  // the hinted register first, as we might want to use that one. Only
4166  // count full instructions for free ranges, as an instruction's internal
4167  // positions do not help but might shadow a hinted register. This is
4168  // typically the case for function calls, where all registered are
4169  // cloberred after the call except for the argument registers, which are
4170  // set before the call. Hence, the argument registers always get ignored,
4171  // as their available time is shorter.
4172  int reg = (hint_reg == kUnassignedRegister) ? codes[0] : hint_reg;
4173  int current_free = free_until_pos[reg].ToInstructionIndex();
4174  for (int i = 0; i < num_codes; ++i) {
4175  int code = codes[i];
4176  // Prefer registers that have no fixed uses to avoid blocking later hints.
4177  // We use the first register that has no fixed uses to ensure we use
4178  // byte addressable registers in ia32 first.
4179  int candidate_free = free_until_pos[code].ToInstructionIndex();
4180  TRACE("Register %s in free until %d\n", RegisterName(code), candidate_free);
4181  if ((candidate_free > current_free) ||
4182  (candidate_free == current_free && reg != hint_reg &&
4183  (data()->HasFixedUse(current->representation(), reg) &&
4184  !data()->HasFixedUse(current->representation(), code)))) {
4185  reg = code;
4186  current_free = candidate_free;
4187  }
4188  }
4189 
4190  return reg;
4191 }
4192 
4193 bool LinearScanAllocator::TryAllocateFreeReg(
4194  LiveRange* current, base::Vector<const LifetimePosition> free_until_pos) {
4195  // Compute register hint, if such exists.
4196  int hint_reg = kUnassignedRegister;
4197  current->RegisterFromControlFlow(&hint_reg) ||
4198  current->RegisterFromFirstHint(&hint_reg) ||
4199  current->RegisterFromBundle(&hint_reg);
4200 
4201  int reg =
4202  PickRegisterThatIsAvailableLongest(current, hint_reg, free_until_pos);
4203 
4204  LifetimePosition pos = free_until_pos[reg];
4205 
4206  if (pos <= current->Start()) {
4207  // All registers are blocked.
4208  return false;
4209  }
4210 
4211  if (pos < current->End()) {
4212  // Register reg is available at the range start but becomes blocked before
4213  // the range end. Split current before the position where it becomes
4214  // blocked. Shift the split position to the last gap position. This is to
4215  // ensure that if a connecting move is needed, that move coincides with the
4216  // start of the range that it defines. See crbug.com/1182985.
4217  LifetimePosition gap_pos =
4218  pos.IsGapPosition() ? pos : pos.FullStart().End();
4219  if (gap_pos <= current->Start()) return false;
4220  LiveRange* tail = SplitRangeAt(current, gap_pos);
4221  AddToUnhandled(tail);
4222 
4223  // Try to allocate preferred register once more.
4224  if (TryAllocatePreferredReg(current, free_until_pos)) return true;
4225  }
4226 
4227  // Register reg is available at the range start and is free until the range
4228  // end.
4229  DCHECK_GE(pos, current->End());
4230  TRACE("Assigning free reg %s to live range %d:%d\n", RegisterName(reg),
4231  current->TopLevel()->vreg(), current->relative_id());
4232  SetLiveRangeAssignedRegister(current, reg);
4233 
4234  return true;
4235 }
4236 
4237 void LinearScanAllocator::AllocateBlockedReg(LiveRange* current,
4238  SpillMode spill_mode) {
4239  UsePosition* register_use = current->NextRegisterPosition(current->Start());
4240  if (register_use == nullptr) {
4241  // There is no use in the current live range that requires a register.
4242  // We can just spill it.
4243  LiveRange* begin_spill = nullptr;
4244  LifetimePosition spill_pos = FindOptimalSpillingPos(
4245  current, current->Start(), spill_mode, &begin_spill);
4246  MaybeSpillPreviousRanges(begin_spill, spill_pos, current);
4247  Spill(current, spill_mode);
4248  return;
4249  }
4250 
4251  MachineRepresentation rep = current->representation();
4252 
4253  // use_pos keeps track of positions a register/alias is used at.
4254  // block_pos keeps track of positions where a register/alias is blocked
4255  // from.
4256  base::EmbeddedVector<LifetimePosition, RegisterConfiguration::kMaxRegisters>
4257  use_pos(LifetimePosition::MaxPosition());
4258  base::EmbeddedVector<LifetimePosition, RegisterConfiguration::kMaxRegisters>
4259  block_pos(LifetimePosition::MaxPosition());
4260 
4261  for (LiveRange* range : active_live_ranges()) {
4262  int cur_reg = range->assigned_register();
4263  bool is_fixed_or_cant_spill =
4264  range->TopLevel()->IsFixed() || !range->CanBeSpilled(current->Start());
4265  if (kFPAliasing != AliasingKind::kCombine || !check_fp_aliasing()) {
4266  if (is_fixed_or_cant_spill) {
4267  block_pos[cur_reg] = use_pos[cur_reg] =
4268  LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(0);
4269  } else {
4270  DCHECK_NE(LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(0),
4271  block_pos[cur_reg]);
4272  use_pos[cur_reg] =
4273  range->NextLifetimePositionRegisterIsBeneficial(current->Start());
4274  }
4275  } else {
4276  int alias_base_index = -1;
4277  int aliases = data()->config()->GetAliases(
4278  range->representation(), cur_reg, rep, &alias_base_index);
4279  DCHECK(aliases > 0 || (aliases == 0 && alias_base_index == -1));
4280  while (aliases--) {
4281  int aliased_reg = alias_base_index + aliases;
4282  if (is_fixed_or_cant_spill) {
4283  block_pos[aliased_reg] = use_pos[aliased_reg] =
4284  LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(0);
4285  } else {
4286  use_pos[aliased_reg] =
4287  std::min(block_pos[aliased_reg],
4288  range->NextLifetimePositionRegisterIsBeneficial(
4289  current->Start()));
4290  }
4291  }
4292  }
4293  }
4294 
4295  for (int cur_reg = 0; cur_reg < num_registers(); ++cur_reg) {
4296  SlowDCheckInactiveLiveRangesIsSorted(cur_reg);
4297  for (LiveRange* range : inactive_live_ranges(cur_reg)) {
4298  DCHECK(range->End() > current->Start());
4299  DCHECK_EQ(range->assigned_register(), cur_reg);
4300  bool is_fixed = range->TopLevel()->IsFixed();
4301 
4302  // Don't perform costly intersections if they are guaranteed to not update
4303  // block_pos or use_pos.
4304  // TODO(mtrofin): extend to aliased ranges, too.
4305  if ((kFPAliasing != AliasingKind::kCombine || !check_fp_aliasing())) {
4306  DCHECK_LE(use_pos[cur_reg], block_pos[cur_reg]);
4307  if (block_pos[cur_reg] <= range->NextStart()) break;
4308  if (!is_fixed && use_pos[cur_reg] <= range->NextStart()) continue;
4309  }
4310 
4311  LifetimePosition next_intersection = range->FirstIntersection(current);
4312  if (!next_intersection.IsValid()) continue;
4313 
4314  if (kFPAliasing != AliasingKind::kCombine || !check_fp_aliasing()) {
4315  if (is_fixed) {
4316  block_pos[cur_reg] = std::min(block_pos[cur_reg], next_intersection);
4317  use_pos[cur_reg] = std::min(block_pos[cur_reg], use_pos[cur_reg]);
4318  } else {
4319  use_pos[cur_reg] = std::min(use_pos[cur_reg], next_intersection);
4320  }
4321  } else {
4322  int alias_base_index = -1;
4323  int aliases = data()->config()->GetAliases(
4324  range->representation(), cur_reg, rep, &alias_base_index);
4325  DCHECK(aliases > 0 || (aliases == 0 && alias_base_index == -1));
4326  while (aliases--) {
4327  int aliased_reg = alias_base_index + aliases;
4328  if (is_fixed) {
4329  block_pos[aliased_reg] =
4330  std::min(block_pos[aliased_reg], next_intersection);
4331  use_pos[aliased_reg] =
4332  std::min(block_pos[aliased_reg], use_pos[aliased_reg]);
4333  } else {
4334  use_pos[aliased_reg] =
4335  std::min(use_pos[aliased_reg], next_intersection);
4336  }
4337  }
4338  }
4339  }
4340  }
4341 
4342  // Compute register hint if it exists.
4343  int hint_reg = kUnassignedRegister;
4344  current->RegisterFromControlFlow(&hint_reg) ||
4345  register_use->HintRegister(&hint_reg) ||
4346  current->RegisterFromBundle(&hint_reg);
4347  int reg = PickRegisterThatIsAvailableLongest(current, hint_reg, use_pos);
4348 
4349  if (use_pos[reg] < register_use->pos()) {
4350  // If there is a gap position before the next register use, we can
4351  // spill until there. The gap position will then fit the fill move.
4352  if (LifetimePosition::ExistsGapPositionBetween(current->Start(),
4353  register_use->pos())) {
4354  SpillBetween(current, current->Start(), register_use->pos(), spill_mode);
4355  return;
4356  }
4357  }
4358 
4359  // When in deferred spilling mode avoid stealing registers beyond the current
4360  // deferred region. This is required as we otherwise might spill an inactive
4361  // range with a start outside of deferred code and that would not be reloaded.
4362  LifetimePosition new_end = current->End();
4363  if (spill_mode == SpillMode::kSpillDeferred) {
4364  InstructionBlock* deferred_block =
4365  code()->GetInstructionBlock(current->Start().ToInstructionIndex());
4366  new_end =
4367  std::min(new_end, LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(
4368  LastDeferredInstructionIndex(deferred_block)));
4369  }
4370 
4371  // We couldn't spill until the next register use. Split before the register
4372  // is blocked, if applicable.
4373  if (block_pos[reg] < new_end) {
4374  // Register becomes blocked before the current range end. Split before that
4375  // position.
4376  new_end = block_pos[reg].Start();
4377  }
4378 
4379  // If there is no register available at all, we can only spill this range.
4380  // Happens for instance on entry to deferred code where registers might
4381  // become blocked yet we aim to reload ranges.
4382  if (new_end == current->Start()) {
4383  SpillBetween(current, new_end, register_use->pos(), spill_mode);
4384  return;
4385  }
4386 
4387  // Split at the new end if we found one.
4388  if (new_end != current->End()) {
4389  LiveRange* tail = SplitBetween(current, current->Start(), new_end);
4390  AddToUnhandled(tail);
4391  }
4392 
4393  // Register reg is not blocked for the whole range.
4394  DCHECK(block_pos[reg] >= current->End());
4395  TRACE("Assigning blocked reg %s to live range %d:%d\n", RegisterName(reg),
4396  current->TopLevel()->vreg(), current->relative_id());
4397  SetLiveRangeAssignedRegister(current, reg);
4398 
4399  // This register was not free. Thus we need to find and spill
4400  // parts of active and inactive live regions that use the same register
4401  // at the same lifetime positions as current.
4402  SplitAndSpillIntersecting(current, spill_mode);
4403 }
4404 
4405 void LinearScanAllocator::SplitAndSpillIntersecting(LiveRange* current,
4406  SpillMode spill_mode) {
4407  DCHECK(current->HasRegisterAssigned());
4408  int reg = current->assigned_register();
4409  LifetimePosition split_pos = current->Start();
4410  for (auto it = active_live_ranges().begin();
4411  it != active_live_ranges().end();) {
4412  LiveRange* range = *it;
4413  if (kFPAliasing != AliasingKind::kCombine || !check_fp_aliasing()) {
4414  if (range->assigned_register() != reg) {
4415  ++it;
4416  continue;
4417  }
4418  } else {
4419  if (!data()->config()->AreAliases(current->representation(), reg,
4420  range->representation(),
4421  range->assigned_register())) {
4422  ++it;
4423  continue;
4424  }
4425  }
4426 
4427  UsePosition* next_pos = range->NextRegisterPosition(current->Start());
4428  LiveRange* begin_spill = nullptr;
4429  LifetimePosition spill_pos =
4430  FindOptimalSpillingPos(range, split_pos, spill_mode, &begin_spill);
4431  MaybeSpillPreviousRanges(begin_spill, spill_pos, range);
4432  if (next_pos == nullptr) {
4433  SpillAfter(range, spill_pos, spill_mode);
4434  } else {
4435  // When spilling between spill_pos and next_pos ensure that the range
4436  // remains spilled at least until the start of the current live range.
4437  // This guarantees that we will not introduce new unhandled ranges that
4438  // start before the current range as this violates allocation invariants
4439  // and will lead to an inconsistent state of active and inactive
4440  // live-ranges: ranges are allocated in order of their start positions,
4441  // ranges are retired from active/inactive when the start of the
4442  // current live-range is larger than their end.
4443  DCHECK(LifetimePosition::ExistsGapPositionBetween(current->Start(),
4444  next_pos->pos()));
4445  SpillBetweenUntil(range, spill_pos, current->Start(), next_pos->pos(),
4446  spill_mode);
4447  }
4448  it = ActiveToHandled(it);
4449  }
4450 
4451  for (int cur_reg = 0; cur_reg < num_registers(); ++cur_reg) {
4452  if (kFPAliasing != AliasingKind::kCombine || !check_fp_aliasing()) {
4453  if (cur_reg != reg) continue;
4454  }
4455  SlowDCheckInactiveLiveRangesIsSorted(cur_reg);
4456  for (auto it = inactive_live_ranges(cur_reg).begin();
4457  it != inactive_live_ranges(cur_reg).end();) {
4458  LiveRange* range = *it;
4459  if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kCombine && check_fp_aliasing() &&
4460  !data()->config()->AreAliases(current->representation(), reg,
4461  range->representation(), cur_reg)) {
4462  ++it;
4463  continue;
4464  }
4465  DCHECK(range->End() > current->Start());
4466  if (range->TopLevel()->IsFixed()) {
4467  ++it;
4468  continue;
4469  }
4470 
4471  LifetimePosition next_intersection = range->FirstIntersection(current);
4472  if (next_intersection.IsValid()) {
4473  UsePosition* next_pos = range->NextRegisterPosition(current->Start());
4474  if (next_pos == nullptr) {
4475  SpillAfter(range, split_pos, spill_mode);
4476  } else {
4477  next_intersection = std::min(next_intersection, next_pos->pos());
4478  SpillBetween(range, split_pos, next_intersection, spill_mode);
4479  }
4480  it = InactiveToHandled(it);
4481  } else {
4482  ++it;
4483  }
4484  }
4485  }
4486 }
4487 
4488 bool LinearScanAllocator::TryReuseSpillForPhi(TopLevelLiveRange* range) {
4489  if (!range->is_phi()) return false;
4490 
4491  DCHECK(!range->HasSpillOperand());
4492  // Check how many operands belong to the same bundle as the output.
4493  LiveRangeBundle* out_bundle = range->get_bundle();
4494  RegisterAllocationData::PhiMapValue* phi_map_value =
4495  data()->GetPhiMapValueFor(range);
4496  const PhiInstruction* phi = phi_map_value->phi();
4497  const InstructionBlock* block = phi_map_value->block();
4498  // Count the number of spilled operands.
4499  size_t spilled_count = 0;
4500  for (size_t i = 0; i < phi->operands().size(); i++) {
4501  int op = phi->operands()[i];
4502  TopLevelLiveRange* op_range = data()->GetLiveRangeFor(op);
4503  if (!op_range->HasSpillRange() || op_range->get_bundle() != out_bundle)
4504  continue;
4505  const InstructionBlock* pred =
4506  code()->InstructionBlockAt(block->predecessors()[i]);
4507  LifetimePosition pred_end =
4508  LifetimePosition::InstructionFromInstructionIndex(
4509  pred->last_instruction_index());
4510  LiveRange* op_range_child = op_range->GetChildCovers(pred_end);
4511  if (op_range_child != nullptr && op_range_child->spilled()) {
4512  spilled_count++;
4513  }
4514  }
4515 
4516  // Only continue if more than half of the operands are spilled to the same
4517  // slot (because part of same bundle).
4518  if (spilled_count * 2 <= phi->operands().size()) {
4519  return false;
4520  }
4521 
4522  // If the range does not need register soon, spill it to the merged
4523  // spill range.
4524  LifetimePosition next_pos = range->Start();
4525  if (next_pos.IsGapPosition()) next_pos = next_pos.NextStart();
4526  UsePosition* pos = range->NextUsePositionRegisterIsBeneficial(next_pos);
4527  if (pos == nullptr) {
4528  Spill(range, SpillMode::kSpillAtDefinition);
4529  return true;
4530  } else if (pos->pos() > range->Start().NextStart()) {
4531  SpillBetween(range, range->Start(), pos->pos(),
4532  SpillMode::kSpillAtDefinition);
4533  return true;
4534  }
4535  return false;
4536 }
4537 
4538 void LinearScanAllocator::SpillAfter(LiveRange* range, LifetimePosition pos,
4539  SpillMode spill_mode) {
4540  LiveRange* second_part = SplitRangeAt(range, pos);
4541  Spill(second_part, spill_mode);
4542 }
4543 
4544 void LinearScanAllocator::SpillBetween(LiveRange* range, LifetimePosition start,
4545  LifetimePosition end,
4546  SpillMode spill_mode) {
4547  SpillBetweenUntil(range, start, start, end, spill_mode);
4548 }
4549 
4550 void LinearScanAllocator::SpillBetweenUntil(LiveRange* range,
4551  LifetimePosition start,
4552  LifetimePosition until,
4553  LifetimePosition end,
4554  SpillMode spill_mode) {
4555  CHECK(start < end);
4556  LiveRange* second_part = SplitRangeAt(range, start);
4557 
4558  if (second_part->Start() < end) {
4559  // The split result intersects with [start, end[.
4560  // Split it at position between ]start+1, end[, spill the middle part
4561  // and put the rest to unhandled.
4562 
4563  // Make sure that the third part always starts after the start of the
4564  // second part, as that likely is the current position of the register
4565  // allocator and we cannot add ranges to unhandled that start before
4566  // the current position.
4567  LifetimePosition split_start = std::max(second_part->Start().End(), until);
4568 
4569  // If end is an actual use (which it typically is) we have to split
4570  // so that there is a gap before so that we have space for moving the
4571  // value into its position.
4572  // However, if we have no choice, split right where asked.
4573  LifetimePosition third_part_end =
4574  std::max(split_start, end.PrevStart().End());
4575  // Instead of spliting right after or even before the block boundary,
4576  // split on the boumndary to avoid extra moves.
4577  if (data()->IsBlockBoundary(end.Start())) {
4578  third_part_end = std::max(split_start, end.Start());
4579  }
4580 
4581  LiveRange* third_part =
4582  SplitBetween(second_part, split_start, third_part_end);
4583  if (GetInstructionBlock(data()->code(), second_part->Start())
4584  ->IsDeferred()) {
4585  // Try to use the same register as before.
4586  TRACE("Setting control flow hint for %d:%d to %s\n",
4587  third_part->TopLevel()->vreg(), third_part->relative_id(),
4588  RegisterName(range->controlflow_hint()));
4589  third_part->set_controlflow_hint(range->controlflow_hint());
4590  }
4591 
4592  AddToUnhandled(third_part);
4593  // This can happen, even if we checked for start < end above, as we fiddle
4594  // with the end location. However, we are guaranteed to be after or at
4595  // until, so this is fine.
4596  if (third_part != second_part) {
4597  Spill(second_part, spill_mode);
4598  }
4599  } else {
4600  // The split result does not intersect with [start, end[.
4601  // Nothing to spill. Just put it to unhandled as whole.
4602  AddToUnhandled(second_part);
4603  }
4604 }
4605 
4606 OperandAssigner::OperandAssigner(RegisterAllocationData* data) : data_(data) {}
4607 
4608 void OperandAssigner::DecideSpillingMode() {
4609  for (auto range : data()->live_ranges()) {
4610  data()->tick_counter()->TickAndMaybeEnterSafepoint();
4611  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(range);
4612  if (range->IsSpilledOnlyInDeferredBlocks(data())) {
4613  // If the range is spilled only in deferred blocks and starts in
4614  // a non-deferred block, we transition its representation here so
4615  // that the LiveRangeConnector processes them correctly. If,
4616  // however, they start in a deferred block, we uograde them to
4617  // spill at definition, as that definition is in a deferred block
4618  // anyway. While this is an optimization, the code in LiveRangeConnector
4619  // relies on it!
4620  if (GetInstructionBlock(data()->code(), range->Start())->IsDeferred()) {
4621  TRACE("Live range %d is spilled and alive in deferred code only\n",
4622  range->vreg());
4623  range->TransitionRangeToSpillAtDefinition();
4624  } else {
4625  TRACE("Live range %d is spilled deferred code only but alive outside\n",
4626  range->vreg());
4627  range->TransitionRangeToDeferredSpill(data()->allocation_zone());
4628  }
4629  }
4630  }
4631 }
4632 
4633 void OperandAssigner::AssignSpillSlots() {
4634  ZoneVector<SpillRange*> spill_ranges(data()->allocation_zone());
4635  for (const TopLevelLiveRange* range : data()->live_ranges()) {
4636  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(range);
4637  if (range->HasSpillRange()) {
4638  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(range->GetSpillRange());
4639  spill_ranges.push_back(range->GetSpillRange());
4640  }
4641  }
4642  // At this point, the `SpillRange`s for all `TopLevelLiveRange`s should be
4643  // unique, since none have been merged yet.
4644  DCHECK_EQ(spill_ranges.size(),
4645  std::set(spill_ranges.begin(), spill_ranges.end()).size());
4646 
4647  // Merge all `SpillRange`s that belong to the same `LiveRangeBundle`.
4648  for (const TopLevelLiveRange* range : data()->live_ranges()) {
4649  data()->tick_counter()->TickAndMaybeEnterSafepoint();
4650  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(range);
4651  if (range->get_bundle() != nullptr) {
4652  range->get_bundle()->MergeSpillRangesAndClear();
4653  }
4654  }
4655 
4656  // Now merge *all* disjoint, non-empty `SpillRange`s.
4657  // Formerly, this merging was O(n^2) in the number of `SpillRange`s, which
4658  // then dominated compile time (>40%) for some pathological cases,
4659  // e.g., https://crbug.com/v8/14133.
4660  // Now, we allow only `kMaxRetries` unsuccessful merges with directly
4661  // following `SpillRange`s. After each `kMaxRetries`, we exponentially
4662  // increase the stride, which limits the inner loop to O(log n) and thus
4663  // the overall merging to O(n * log n).
4664 
4665  // The merging above may have left some `SpillRange`s empty, remove them.
4666  SpillRange** end_nonempty =
4667  std::remove_if(spill_ranges.begin(), spill_ranges.end(),
4668  [](const SpillRange* range) { return range->IsEmpty(); });
4669  for (SpillRange** range_it = spill_ranges.begin(); range_it < end_nonempty;
4670  ++range_it) {
4671  data()->tick_counter()->TickAndMaybeEnterSafepoint();
4672  SpillRange* range = *range_it;
4673  DCHECK(!range->IsEmpty());
4674  constexpr size_t kMaxRetries = 1000;
4675  size_t retries = kMaxRetries;
4676  size_t stride = 1;
4677  for (SpillRange** other_it = range_it + 1; other_it < end_nonempty;
4678  other_it += stride) {
4679  SpillRange* other = *other_it;
4680  DCHECK(!other->IsEmpty());
4681  if (range->TryMerge(other)) {
4682  DCHECK(other->IsEmpty());
4683  std::iter_swap(other_it, --end_nonempty);
4684  } else if (--retries == 0) {
4685  retries = kMaxRetries;
4686  stride *= 2;
4687  }
4688  }
4689  }
4690  spill_ranges.erase(end_nonempty, spill_ranges.end());
4691 
4692  // Allocate slots for the merged spill ranges.
4693  for (SpillRange* range : spill_ranges) {
4694  data()->tick_counter()->TickAndMaybeEnterSafepoint();
4695  DCHECK(!range->IsEmpty());
4696  if (!range->HasSlot()) {
4697  // Allocate a new operand referring to the spill slot, aligned to the
4698  // operand size.
4699  int width = range->byte_width();
4700  int index = data()->frame()->AllocateSpillSlot(width, width);
4701  range->set_assigned_slot(index);
4702  }
4703  }
4704 }
4705 
4706 void OperandAssigner::CommitAssignment() {
4707  const size_t live_ranges_size = data()->live_ranges().size();
4708  for (TopLevelLiveRange* top_range : data()->live_ranges()) {
4709  data()->tick_counter()->TickAndMaybeEnterSafepoint();
4710  CHECK_EQ(live_ranges_size,
4711  data()->live_ranges().size()); // TODO(neis): crbug.com/831822
4712  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(top_range);
4713  if (top_range->IsEmpty()) continue;
4714  InstructionOperand spill_operand;
4715  if (top_range->HasSpillOperand()) {
4716  auto it = data()->slot_for_const_range().find(top_range);
4717  if (it != data()->slot_for_const_range().end()) {
4718  spill_operand = *it->second;
4719  } else {
4720  spill_operand = *top_range->GetSpillOperand();
4721  }
4722  } else if (top_range->HasSpillRange()) {
4723  spill_operand = top_range->GetSpillRangeOperand();
4724  }
4725  if (top_range->is_phi()) {
4726  data()->GetPhiMapValueFor(top_range)->CommitAssignment(
4727  top_range->GetAssignedOperand());
4728  }
4729  for (LiveRange* range = top_range; range != nullptr;
4730  range = range->next()) {
4731  InstructionOperand assigned = range->GetAssignedOperand();
4732  DCHECK(!assigned.IsUnallocated());
4733  range->ConvertUsesToOperand(assigned, spill_operand);
4734  }
4735 
4736  if (!spill_operand.IsInvalid()) {
4737  // If this top level range has a child spilled in a deferred block, we use
4738  // the range and control flow connection mechanism instead of spilling at
4739  // definition. Refer to the ConnectLiveRanges and ResolveControlFlow
4740  // phases. Normally, when we spill at definition, we do not insert a
4741  // connecting move when a successor child range is spilled - because the
4742  // spilled range picks up its value from the slot which was assigned at
4743  // definition. For ranges that are determined to spill only in deferred
4744  // blocks, we let ConnectLiveRanges and ResolveControlFlow find the blocks
4745  // where a spill operand is expected, and then finalize by inserting the
4746  // spills in the deferred blocks dominators.
4747  if (!top_range->IsSpilledOnlyInDeferredBlocks(data()) &&
4748  !top_range->HasGeneralSpillRange()) {
4749  // Spill at definition if the range isn't spilled in a way that will be
4750  // handled later.
4751  top_range->FilterSpillMoves(data(), spill_operand);
4752  top_range->CommitSpillMoves(data(), spill_operand);
4753  }
4754  }
4755  }
4756 }
4757 
4758 ReferenceMapPopulator::ReferenceMapPopulator(RegisterAllocationData* data)
4759  : data_(data) {}
4760 
4761 bool ReferenceMapPopulator::SafePointsAreInOrder() const {
4762  int safe_point = 0;
4763  for (ReferenceMap* map : *data()->code()->reference_maps()) {
4764  if (safe_point > map->instruction_position()) return false;
4765  safe_point = map->instruction_position();
4766  }
4767  return true;
4768 }
4769 
4770 void ReferenceMapPopulator::PopulateReferenceMaps() {
4771  DCHECK(SafePointsAreInOrder());
4772  // Map all delayed references.
4773  for (RegisterAllocationData::DelayedReference& delayed_reference :
4774  data()->delayed_references()) {
4775  delayed_reference.map->RecordReference(
4776  AllocatedOperand::cast(*delayed_reference.operand));
4777  }
4778  // Iterate over all safe point positions and record a pointer
4779  // for all spilled live ranges at this point.
4780  int last_range_start = 0;
4781  const ReferenceMaps* reference_maps = data()->code()->reference_maps();
4782  ReferenceMaps::const_iterator first_it = reference_maps->begin();
4783  const size_t live_ranges_size = data()->live_ranges().size();
4784  // Select subset of `TopLevelLiveRange`s to process, sort them by their start.
4785  ZoneVector<TopLevelLiveRange*> candidate_ranges(data()->allocation_zone());
4786  candidate_ranges.reserve(data()->live_ranges().size());
4787  for (TopLevelLiveRange* range : data()->live_ranges()) {
4788  CHECK_EQ(live_ranges_size,
4789  data()->live_ranges().size()); // TODO(neis): crbug.com/831822
4790  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(range);
4791  // Skip non-reference values.
4792  if (!data()->code()->IsReference(range->vreg())) continue;
4793  // Skip empty live ranges.
4794  if (range->IsEmpty()) continue;
4795  if (range->has_preassigned_slot()) continue;
4796  candidate_ranges.push_back(range);
4797  }
4798  std::sort(candidate_ranges.begin(), candidate_ranges.end(),
4799  LiveRangeOrdering());
4800  for (TopLevelLiveRange* range : candidate_ranges) {
4801  // Find the extent of the range and its children.
4802  int start = range->Start().ToInstructionIndex();
4803  int end = range->Children().back()->End().ToInstructionIndex();
4804 
4805  // Ranges should be sorted, so that the first reference map in the current
4806  // live range has to be after {first_it}.
4807  DCHECK_LE(last_range_start, start);
4808  last_range_start = start;
4809  USE(last_range_start);
4810 
4811  // Step across all the safe points that are before the start of this range,
4812  // recording how far we step in order to save doing this for the next range.
4813  for (; first_it != reference_maps->end(); ++first_it) {
4814  ReferenceMap* map = *first_it;
4815  if (map->instruction_position() >= start) break;
4816  }
4817 
4818  InstructionOperand spill_operand;
4819  if (((range->HasSpillOperand() &&
4820  !range->GetSpillOperand()->IsConstant()) ||
4821  range->HasSpillRange())) {
4822  if (range->HasSpillOperand()) {
4823  spill_operand = *range->GetSpillOperand();
4824  } else {
4825  spill_operand = range->GetSpillRangeOperand();
4826  }
4827  DCHECK(spill_operand.IsStackSlot());
4828  DCHECK(CanBeTaggedOrCompressedPointer(
4829  AllocatedOperand::cast(spill_operand).representation()));
4830  }
4831 
4832  LiveRange* cur = nullptr;
4833  // Step through the safe points to see whether they are in the range.
4834  for (auto it = first_it; it != reference_maps->end(); ++it) {
4835  ReferenceMap* map = *it;
4836  int safe_point = map->instruction_position();
4837 
4838  // The safe points are sorted so we can stop searching here.
4839  if (safe_point - 1 > end) break;
4840 
4841  // Advance to the next active range that covers the current
4842  // safe point position.
4843  LifetimePosition safe_point_pos =
4844  LifetimePosition::InstructionFromInstructionIndex(safe_point);
4845 
4846  // Search for the child range (cur) that covers safe_point_pos. If we
4847  // don't find it before the children pass safe_point_pos, keep cur at
4848  // the last child, because the next safe_point_pos may be covered by cur.
4849  // This may happen if cur has more than one interval, and the current
4850  // safe_point_pos is in between intervals.
4851  // For that reason, cur may be at most the last child.
4852  // Use binary search for the first iteration, then linear search after.
4853  bool found = false;
4854  if (cur == nullptr) {
4855  cur = range->GetChildCovers(safe_point_pos);
4856  found = cur != nullptr;
4857  } else {
4858  while (!found) {
4859  if (cur->Covers(safe_point_pos)) {
4860  found = true;
4861  } else {
4862  LiveRange* next = cur->next();
4863  if (next == nullptr || next->Start() > safe_point_pos) {
4864  break;
4865  }
4866  cur = next;
4867  }
4868  }
4869  }
4870 
4871  if (!found) {
4872  continue;
4873  }
4874 
4875  // Check if the live range is spilled and the safe point is after
4876  // the spill position.
4877  int spill_index = range->IsSpilledOnlyInDeferredBlocks(data()) ||
4878  range->LateSpillingSelected()
4879  ? cur->Start().ToInstructionIndex()
4880  : range->spill_start_index();
4881 
4882  if (!spill_operand.IsInvalid() && safe_point >= spill_index) {
4883  TRACE("Pointer for range %d (spilled at %d) at safe point %d\n",
4884  range->vreg(), spill_index, safe_point);
4885  map->RecordReference(AllocatedOperand::cast(spill_operand));
4886  }
4887 
4888  if (!cur->spilled()) {
4889  TRACE(
4890  "Pointer in register for range %d:%d (start at %d) "
4891  "at safe point %d\n",
4892  range->vreg(), cur->relative_id(), cur->Start().value(),
4893  safe_point);
4894  InstructionOperand operand = cur->GetAssignedOperand();
4895  DCHECK(!operand.IsStackSlot());
4896  DCHECK(CanBeTaggedOrCompressedPointer(
4897  AllocatedOperand::cast(operand).representation()));
4898  map->RecordReference(AllocatedOperand::cast(operand));
4899  }
4900  }
4901  }
4902 }
4903 
4904 LiveRangeConnector::LiveRangeConnector(RegisterAllocationData* data)
4905  : data_(data) {}
4906 
4907 bool LiveRangeConnector::CanEagerlyResolveControlFlow(
4908  const InstructionBlock* block) const {
4909  if (block->PredecessorCount() != 1) return false;
4910  return block->predecessors()[0].IsNext(block->rpo_number());
4911 }
4912 
4913 void LiveRangeConnector::ResolveControlFlow(Zone* local_zone) {
4914  ZoneVector<SparseBitVector*>& live_in_sets = data()->live_in_sets();
4915  for (const InstructionBlock* block : code()->instruction_blocks()) {
4916  if (CanEagerlyResolveControlFlow(block)) continue;
4917  SparseBitVector* live = live_in_sets[block->rpo_number().ToInt()];
4918  for (int vreg : *live) {
4919  data()->tick_counter()->TickAndMaybeEnterSafepoint();
4920  TopLevelLiveRange* live_range = data()->live_ranges()[vreg];
4921  LifetimePosition cur_start = LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(
4922  block->first_instruction_index());
4923  LiveRange* cur_range = live_range->GetChildCovers(cur_start);
4924  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(cur_range);
4925  if (cur_range->spilled()) continue;
4926 
4927  for (const RpoNumber& pred : block->predecessors()) {
4928  // Find ranges that may need to be connected.
4929  const InstructionBlock* pred_block = code()->InstructionBlockAt(pred);
4930  LifetimePosition pred_end =
4931  LifetimePosition::InstructionFromInstructionIndex(
4932  pred_block->last_instruction_index());
4933  // We don't need to perform the O(log n) search if we already know it
4934  // will be the same range.
4935  if (cur_range->CanCover(pred_end)) continue;
4936  LiveRange* pred_range = live_range->GetChildCovers(pred_end);
4937  // This search should always succeed because the `vreg` associated to
4938  // this `live_range` must be live out in all predecessor blocks.
4939  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(pred_range);
4940  // Since the `cur_range` did not cover `pred_end` earlier, the found
4941  // `pred_range` must be different.
4942  DCHECK_NE(cur_range, pred_range);
4943 
4944  InstructionOperand pred_op = pred_range->GetAssignedOperand();
4945  InstructionOperand cur_op = cur_range->GetAssignedOperand();
4946  if (pred_op.Equals(cur_op)) continue;
4947 
4948  if (!pred_op.IsAnyRegister() && cur_op.IsAnyRegister()) {
4949  // We're doing a reload.
4950  // We don't need to, if:
4951  // 1) there's no register use in this block, and
4952  // 2) the range ends before the block does, and
4953  // 3) we don't have a successor, or the successor is spilled.
4954  LifetimePosition block_start =
4955  LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(block->code_start());
4956  LifetimePosition block_end =
4957  LifetimePosition::GapFromInstructionIndex(block->code_end());
4958  // Note that this is not the successor if we have control flow!
4959  // However, in the following condition, we only refer to it if it
4960  // begins in the current block, in which case we can safely declare it
4961  // to be the successor.
4962  const LiveRange* successor = cur_range->next();
4963  if (cur_range->End() < block_end &&
4964  (successor == nullptr || successor->spilled())) {
4965  // verify point 1: no register use. We can go to the end of the
4966  // range, since it's all within the block.
4967 
4968  bool uses_reg = false;
4969  for (UsePosition* const* use_pos_it =
4970  cur_range->NextUsePosition(block_start);
4971  use_pos_it != cur_range->positions().end(); ++use_pos_it) {
4972  if ((*use_pos_it)->operand()->IsAnyRegister()) {
4973  uses_reg = true;
4974  break;
4975  }
4976  }
4977  if (!uses_reg) continue;
4978  }
4979  if (cur_range->TopLevel()->IsSpilledOnlyInDeferredBlocks(data()) &&
4980  pred_block->IsDeferred()) {
4981  // The spill location should be defined in pred_block, so add
4982  // pred_block to the list of blocks requiring a spill operand.
4983  TRACE("Adding B%d to list of spill blocks for %d\n",
4984  pred_block->rpo_number().ToInt(),
4985  cur_range->TopLevel()->vreg());
4986  cur_range->TopLevel()
4987  ->GetListOfBlocksRequiringSpillOperands(data())
4988  ->Add(pred_block->rpo_number().ToInt());
4989  }
4990  }
4991  int move_loc = ResolveControlFlow(block, cur_op, pred_block, pred_op);
4992  USE(move_loc);
4993  DCHECK_IMPLIES(
4994  cur_range->TopLevel()->IsSpilledOnlyInDeferredBlocks(data()) &&
4995  !(pred_op.IsAnyRegister() && cur_op.IsAnyRegister()) &&
4996  move_loc != -1,
4997  code()->GetInstructionBlock(move_loc)->IsDeferred());
4998  }
4999  }
5000  }
5001 
5002  // At this stage, we collected blocks needing a spill operand due to reloads
5003  // from ConnectRanges and from ResolveControlFlow. Time to commit the spills
5004  // for deferred blocks. This is a convenient time to commit spills for general
5005  // spill ranges also, because they need to use the LiveRangeFinder.
5006  const size_t live_ranges_size = data()->live_ranges().size();
5007  SpillPlacer spill_placer(data(), local_zone);
5008  for (TopLevelLiveRange* top : data()->live_ranges()) {
5009  CHECK_EQ(live_ranges_size,
5010  data()->live_ranges().size()); // TODO(neis): crbug.com/831822
5011  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(top);
5012  if (top->IsEmpty()) continue;
5013  if (top->IsSpilledOnlyInDeferredBlocks(data())) {
5014  CommitSpillsInDeferredBlocks(top, local_zone);
5015  } else if (top->HasGeneralSpillRange()) {
5016  spill_placer.Add(top);
5017  }
5018  }
5019 }
5020 
5021 int LiveRangeConnector::ResolveControlFlow(const InstructionBlock* block,
5022  const InstructionOperand& cur_op,
5023  const InstructionBlock* pred,
5024  const InstructionOperand& pred_op) {
5025  DCHECK(!pred_op.Equals(cur_op));
5026  int gap_index;
5027  Instruction::GapPosition position;
5028  if (block->PredecessorCount() == 1) {
5029  gap_index = block->first_instruction_index();
5030  position = Instruction::START;
5031  } else {
5032  Instruction* last = code()->InstructionAt(pred->last_instruction_index());
5033  // The connecting move might invalidate uses of the destination operand in
5034  // the deoptimization call. See crbug.com/v8/12218. Omitting the move is
5035  // safe since the deopt call exits the current code.
5036  if (last->IsDeoptimizeCall()) {
5037  return -1;
5038  }
5039  // In every other case the last instruction should not participate in
5040  // register allocation, or it could interfere with the connecting move.
5041  for (size_t i = 0; i < last->InputCount(); ++i) {
5042  DCHECK(last->InputAt(i)->IsImmediate());
5043  }
5044  DCHECK_EQ(1, pred->SuccessorCount());
5045  DCHECK(!code()
5046  ->InstructionAt(pred->last_instruction_index())
5047  ->HasReferenceMap());
5048  gap_index = pred->last_instruction_index();
5049  position = Instruction::END;
5050  }
5051  data()->AddGapMove(gap_index, position, pred_op, cur_op);
5052  return gap_index;
5053 }
5054 
5055 void LiveRangeConnector::ConnectRanges(Zone* local_zone) {
5056  DelayedInsertionMap delayed_insertion_map(local_zone);
5057  const size_t live_ranges_size = data()->live_ranges().size();
5058  for (TopLevelLiveRange* top_range : data()->live_ranges()) {
5059  CHECK_EQ(live_ranges_size,
5060  data()->live_ranges().size()); // TODO(neis): crbug.com/831822
5061  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(top_range);
5062  bool connect_spilled = top_range->IsSpilledOnlyInDeferredBlocks(data());
5063  LiveRange* first_range = top_range;
5064  for (LiveRange *second_range = first_range->next(); second_range != nullptr;
5065  first_range = second_range, second_range = second_range->next()) {
5066  LifetimePosition pos = second_range->Start();
5067  // Add gap move if the two live ranges touch and there is no block
5068  // boundary.
5069  if (second_range->spilled()) continue;
5070  if (first_range->End() != pos) continue;
5071  if (data()->IsBlockBoundary(pos) &&
5072  !CanEagerlyResolveControlFlow(GetInstructionBlock(code(), pos))) {
5073  continue;
5074  }
5075  InstructionOperand prev_operand = first_range->GetAssignedOperand();
5076  InstructionOperand cur_operand = second_range->GetAssignedOperand();
5077  if (prev_operand.Equals(cur_operand)) continue;
5078  bool delay_insertion = false;
5079  Instruction::GapPosition gap_pos;
5080  int gap_index = pos.ToInstructionIndex();
5081  if (connect_spilled && !prev_operand.IsAnyRegister() &&
5082  cur_operand.IsAnyRegister()) {
5083  const InstructionBlock* block = code()->GetInstructionBlock(gap_index);
5084  DCHECK(block->IsDeferred());
5085  // Performing a reload in this block, meaning the spill operand must
5086  // be defined here.
5087  top_range->GetListOfBlocksRequiringSpillOperands(data())->Add(
5088  block->rpo_number().ToInt());
5089  }
5090 
5091  if (pos.IsGapPosition()) {
5092  gap_pos = pos.IsStart() ? Instruction::START : Instruction::END;
5093  } else {
5094  if (pos.IsStart()) {
5095  delay_insertion = true;
5096  } else {
5097  gap_index++;
5098  }
5099  gap_pos = delay_insertion ? Instruction::END : Instruction::START;
5100  }
5101  // Reloads or spills for spilled in deferred blocks ranges must happen
5102  // only in deferred blocks.
5103  DCHECK_IMPLIES(connect_spilled && !(prev_operand.IsAnyRegister() &&
5104  cur_operand.IsAnyRegister()),
